title: easy spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large frying pan, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti and tomato sauces; cover and simmer.
In a medium bowl, combine spinach, cheeses and seasonings.

title: strawberry swirl
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick, add softened cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth and light.
Beat egg whites stiff. Whip cream until stiff and fold with egg whites into cheese mixture.
Crush strawberries to a pulp using a mixer.
Gently whirl half of fruit into cheese mixture and spread over crumbs.
Spoon remaining fruit over top, swirl with a knife.
Freeze; then cover and return to freezer.
Keeps for many days.
Raspberries can be used instead, if desired.

title: heart warming & potato soup
directions: Cook sausage, onion, celery & garlic in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sausage is no longer pink, & drain.

title: orange delight
directions: Pour hot water over jello and marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Set aside.

title: rhubarb strawberry preserves
directions: Bring sugar, rhubarb and pineapple to a boil for 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add strawberry jello; stir until mixed good. Will keep good in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Can in 1/2 pint jar. Nice for gift.

title: best-ever pound cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open oven for one hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit with 4 pieces; mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in Benet pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
melt butter and stir in brown sugar. Pour over biscuits and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch square or tube pan.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce(about 10 servings)
directions: *Substitute turkey or chicken for less fat.

title: bread pudding with peach sauce
directions: Dice bread and put in shallow buttered 1-quart baking dish. Heat milk and margarine only until melted.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat eggs and add while stirring.
Pour over bread.
Add raisins and cinnamon; stir.
Set dish in pan with hot water to half depth of dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable potato soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in covered saucepan until tender. Mash until fluffy.
Add milk; mix well.
Cook remaining vegetables and salt in beef broth in covered saucepan until tender, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend with potato mixture.
Stir in black pepper and butter.
Serve with French bread and tossed salad.
Follow with fresh fruit and cookies.

title: hominy delight
directions: Dissolve cheese in sauteed onions.
Pour into soups.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over hominy and bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add maple flavoring, if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix chicken, celery and pineapple chunks together, then mix salad dressing, mayonnaise and reserved pineapple juice together. Add this to chicken mixture and toss well to coat.

title: chili with beans
directions: Use Dutch oven if not cooking in large pot on fire or stove. Must cook slow.

title: golden glaze ham
directions: Score ham.
Heat 20 minutes per pound at 325°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat until jelly melts.
Spoon glaze over ham.
Delicious.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt shortening and chocolate together.
Beat eggs well; add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly.
Add chocolate mixture and blend.
Add flour and mix well, then stir in nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes for moist brownies or 30 minutes for cake-like brownies.
Cool in pan, then cut in squares.

title: aunt ruby bagwell's biscuits
directions: Mix with a fork; roll in flour.
Cut and dip each biscuit in cooking oil.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Heat oil; cook garlic and onion until soft, then add beef and the seasonings. Cook until crumbly.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese.

title: herbed vegetables
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet.
Add mushrooms and salt.
Cook over medium heat about 3 minutes to cook out moisture in mushrooms. They should be tender, but not limp.
Place mushroom slices on paper towels.
Wipe skillet dry with a paper towel.
Spray with Pam.
Add thyme, chervil and rosemary; saute 30 seconds.
Stir in zucchini, broccoli, mushrooms and red pepper.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and serve.
(measure servings).
Single serving equals 1 cup vegetables.

title: chicken and orange salad
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and while still hot, mix with onion and seasonings; cool.
Add chicken, celery, olives and mayonnaise.
Toss lightly.
Peel oranges and split them into sections.
Cut 1/2 of the sections into small pieces.
Add to mixture.

title: custard float
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Combine with sugar and mix.
Add to sweet milk.
Cook over medium heat.
When thickens (doesn't get real thick), remove from heat.
Add vanilla and blend.
Fold in lightly the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Set aside to cool.
In summer, chill in refrigerator.

title: corn romano(micro magic)
directions: Place corn in a 1-quart microwave casserole and add butter, chives, and Italian seasonings.
Cover and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes; stirring once, until corn is done.
Add garlic powder, olives and cheese and toss lightly to coat.

title: carolyn's junk
directions: Melt chocolate wafers in oil in the top of a double boiler. Pour onto cereal mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread onto 2 cookie sheets.
Let cool and break into pieces.
(Four cups Double Chex cereal may be substituted for any 2 Chex cereals.)
At holiday times, colored wafers may be used instead of the white chocolate wafers.
Store in airtight container.

title: onion rings
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Slice 3 to 4 large onions and separate into rings. Dip rings into batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: bonnie's bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook on high heat for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put in jars and seal immediately.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all but shrimp (may be done in a blender).
Add shrimp.
Great with fancy crackers or Cool Ranch Doritos.

title: scott's cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and sugar in small bowl.
Press over bottom of greased 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate. Beat together all 5 packages of cream cheese, 1 3/4 cup sugar, flour and vanilla in a large bowl until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth.
Stir heavy cream into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (475°) for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 250°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn off oven.
Leave cake in oven for 1 hour.
Open door partway and leave cake in oven for 30 minutes more.
Cool on wire rack to room temperature.
(Cheesecake may crack on top.) Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Wash, hull, and slice strawberries; place in bowl. Sprinkle berries with sugar and refrigerate until sugar dissolves and juice accumulates in bowl. Combine strawberries (juice also), eggs, and oil; mix. Combine dry ingredients (except nuts); mix well with berry mixture. Fold in nuts. Pour into greased and floured bundt pan; bake at 350° for 70 minutes (for 3 small loaf pans, bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°). Allow to cool completely before serving.

title: veg-all salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold or heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes and serve hot.

title: stewed eggplant and tomato
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Boil eggplant until slightly opaque.
Then drain the water; keep separate.
Dice onion and green pepper; saute together with garlic until tender. Add tomatoes with the tomato juice to the onion and pepper until heated.
Mix onion, pepper, tomatoes and croutons with eggplant. Add oregano, basil and Romano cheese to taste.
Bake together at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips and nuts; mix well. Pour into greased and floured 12 x 18-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nut meats on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(Check after 25 minutes.
It may be done.)

title: corn dogs
directions: Roll hot dogs in mixture and deep fry.

title: mexican dip
directions: Prepare the day before on large plate.
Spread the ingredients, beginning with the bean dip as listed, layer, topping with tomato slices.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips, Fritos or crackers.
Great as munch during Super Bowl, bridge club or party.

title: grandma's tomato beef soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a large pan except for the orzo (shells or macaroni).
After beef shank is fully cooked, remove it from the pan.
Let it cool. Cut off meat into bite size pieces and return to pan.
Cook orzo (shells or macaroni) separately until almost done. Add to soup stock and simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with warm French bread.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: layered blueberry delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix the graham cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Put in bottom of glass dish.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: In a saucepan heat cranberry juice cocktail to boiling. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix
cake
per	directions
and pour 1/2 batter in cake pan. Cook
to 10 minutes.
Mix in
double boiler the caramels, butter and Pet milk; melt.	Pour this mixture over baked cake. Now
sprinkle
chocolate
chips
and
nuts over caramel mixture. Now
pour rest of cake batter over this and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cook onion and celery until tender; add butter and mix bread and egg.
Add broth to make moist.
Add this to chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: frango's
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add melted chips, then vanilla and peppermint.
Mix well.
Add 1 egg; mix well, then add the second egg.
Mix until thick.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch
or 10 x 10-inch buttered pan.
Will be 1/2-inch thick.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix powdered sugar, oleo and milk.
Mix in heavy saucepan and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Once it starts to boil, boil 7 minutes or until hardens in cold water.
Next add marshmallow cream; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chip nuts, candy and dates.
Add coconut.
Melt butter and pour over the eggs, sugar, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Add to the nuts, then add flour.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275° or until done.

title: eggs and chips casserole
directions: Combine everything but chips and cheese.
Mix thoroughly but lightly so as not to break up eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with potato chips.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, bake at 375° until heated through.

title: dutch cabbage or sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Do not toss.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Keep covered at least 24 hours.
Toss before serving.
Will keep about 2 weeks.

title: veal scalloppeni
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut veal into 1 1/4-inch cubes.
Roll lightly in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Saute onions in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Saute veal in oil left from onions.
Place veal in casserole along with mushrooms, tomatoes, sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Bake 1 1/2 hours covered, or until fork-tender.

title: potatoes ala mode
directions: Peel and dice cooked potatoes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Bake 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Top with 1/2 cup more cheese and seasoned bread crumbs or cornflakes. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in 1 cup water in large bowl for several minutes. Mash bread with fork.
Add ground beef, onion, Parmesan cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pour tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: oriental fondue
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes. Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Pour broth into fondue pot and heat to boiling.
Place meat in serving dish.
Spread beef with forks or hold with chopsticks and cook in boiling broth 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Serve with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add salt, eggs and vanilla. Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add to the first mixture.
Beat and stir in flour.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and roll into a rectangle.
Spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into pan rolls or shape into circle and snip for T-ring.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon blueberry jam
directions: In large saucepan, crush half of the berries.
Add remaining berries, sugar and jello.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil hard for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into hot clean jelly glasses or jars; seal.
Makes 3 half-pints.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in iron skillet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: refrigerator pie crust
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl the flour, soda, salt, baking powder, syrup and Crisco.
Add 7-Up.
Mix with hand and turn out onto floured board.
Knead until the dough does not stick to your hand.
Place in a plastic bag in refrigerator.
Use as needed for a quick pie crust or cobbler crust.
Will make six crusts and the dough will last for three weeks.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Drain. Add chili beans and Hormel Chili.
For a "soupier" dish add tomato juice.
Simmer until blended.
Remove from heat and let set.
Heat when ready to serve.
Serve with chopped onion and shredded cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan. Should have a nice brown crust on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.
The longer you keep this cake, the more moist it gets.
No flavoring is needed but I add lemon or orange extract sometimes.

title: tuna-broccoli quiche
directions: Thaw and "drain" broccoli between paper towels.
Combine milk, eggs, tuna fish, cheese, dill weed and broccoli and salt in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° (or until knife comes out clean, cutting into center).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving with lemon wedges.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into a loaf.
Roll it in 1 c. chopped walnuts.
Put in wax paper and leave in freezer 24 hours. Thaw and serve with crackers.

title: white lightnin'
directions: Mix together for a quick, easy dip or spread.
Sprinkle with paprika or minced parsley for color.
Good with corn chips.

title: chow mein beef bake
directions: In a large skillet combine beef, celery and onion.
Cook until meat is brown and drain.
Add tomato, mushroom soup, water and half of chow mein noodles.
Stir until blended.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Melt margarine. Saute leeks and celery. Pour in chicken broth and water. Add potatoes and parsley. Simmer 1 hour. Add milk and simmer 15 minutes. Blend flour into 1/4 cup water and stir into soup. Simmer another 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Blend in cream cheese.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
pour into baked graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: orange glaze carrots
directions: *Dilute orange juice with only 1 can of water before measuring.

title: barbecued chicken in the oven
directions: Wash and dry cut up chicken; place pieces, fat side up, in baking pan.
Pour water in pan.
Place sliced onion around chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and mustard seed in sauce pan. Bring to boil and pour on chopped vegetables.
Stir well.
Place in glass container.
Will be good up to 9 days.

title: harvest pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Cook at 350° about 30 minutes.
Yummy.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and boil for about 10 minutes.
Take off the stove and add peanut butter, then add oatmeal.
Spoon off on foil or waxed paper.
Cool for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, bake at 350° for 65 minutes in 2 Pam-sprayed loaf pans.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix coloring and cocoa and let stand.
Beat sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, add color, cocoa and vanilla; beat well again.
Gradually add flour and salt and beat.
Add buttermilk and beat.
Add vinegar and soda; beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in prepared pan.

title: peanut pattie
directions: Bring to boil on medium heat sugar, water and syrup.
When that boils, add peanuts and coloring.
Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add butter.
Beat until mixture is too thick to beat.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: open-face cucumber sandwiches
directions: *Mix cream cheese, Italian dressing mix, and mayonnaise. Whip until creamy.
Spread on slices of party rye.
Lay 2 very thin slices of cucumber on top.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add other ingredients one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in loaf or in cupcakes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be served with a meal or as a dessert.

title: zalabia
directions: Combine cake yeast in the warmed milk
Beat eggs slightly, add melted oleo, sugar and warmed milk and yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix.
You will need more flour, could use as much as 10 lb. of flour depending on size of eggs.
Knead until dough is smooth.
Let rest.
After 2 hours, cut into balls and let rest again.
Roll out like a pizza and cut into squares.
Fry in hot oil and sprinkle sugar, powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
Of course, you can eat plain also.

title: fruit nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, sift flour mixture over fruits and nuts; stir until coated.
Beat eggs until light, add vanilla and pour over mixture; mix well.
Put in greased loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Combine
baking mix, sugar and 1/2 cup cheese.	Add egg and milk.
Mix	well.
Put
in	a
small
greased
loaf
pan. Sprinkle remaining	cheese	on
top.
Pour melted butter over cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy perogie pizza
directions: Prepare package of instant mashed potatoes as directed with water, butter or margarine, milk and salt.
Set aside.
Add 1 can drained sauerkraut.
Mix in 1/2 cup Mozzarella and 1/2 cup Colby, Longhorn or Cheddar cheese and salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Put in blender to thicken.

title: ice cream cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 dish, line the bottom with ice cream bars. Cover the ice cream bars with whipped topping. Sprinkle chopped candy bars over the whipped topping. Seal the dish and store in freezer until ready to serve.

title: hungarian nut rolls(christmas crescents)
directions: Sift together the flour, 1 tsp. salt and 1 tsp. cinnamon into medium size bowl. Add butter and blend with pastry blender (or you can use your hands) until mixture is of a crumbly consistency. Combine, in a separate bowl, the sour cream, egg yolks and 2 Tbsp. lemon juice. Blend into flour mixture until completely mixed. Divide dough into 4 portions, wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper and chill at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: swiss bliss
directions: You will need 20-inch sheet of heavy foil.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in 6 to 7 quarts of water in large kettle.
Boil on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding water to keep 6 to 7 quarts of water at all times.
Remove from heat and remove chicken from water.
Let cool.
Cut all meat from bones into 1/2 to 1-inch size chunks and return to kettle.
Add carrots, celery, onions, tomatoes, chicken concentrate and barley.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add noodles 10 minutes before serving.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: *I use the Oriental flavor kind.

title: southwestern chicken(2 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray 8-inch square baking dish with no-stick cooking spray.
Combine wheat germ and seasonings; set aside.
Combine water and egg white.
Dip chicken into egg mixture and then into wheat germ mixture, coating chicken thoroughly.
Place chicken in prepared pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: hamburger chili macaroni
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning.
Bring to boil.
Add macaroni.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato celery soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Do not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Celery will remain crisp.
Serve topped with unsweetened whipping cream and chopped parsley.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, seasoning and sugar.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce, uncooked lasagna, cottage or Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry delight
directions: In saucepan, cook cranberries, raisins and sugar over low heat, carefully stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple chunks and cool.
Place in a pretty glass bowl.
When cool, cover with broken nutmeats.
Chill before serving.

title: art's rice pudding
directions: Combine water and milk in large pot.
When water and milk get warm, add rice.
When rice is cooked (15 to 20 minutes), stir in rest of ingredients that have been well mixed together.
Stir a few times and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into container.
When pudding is cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut well and drain. Add pepper, onion, celery, pimento and celery seed. Mix sugar, water, vinegar and oil. Pour this over sauerkraut mix and store in refrigerator in covered container.

title: fruit cake
directions: Pour in greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Drain water from vegetables.
To vegetables, mix soup, cheese (broken into pieces) and chopped onion.
Brown beef; drain grease. Add to vegetable mixture.
(If using chicken instead of beef, just add it to mixture.)
Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Use second shell to make top crust; be sure to prick top to let steam escape.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse
peas.
Combine with 2 quarts of water, ham bone, onion, salt,
pepper
and marjoram.
Bring to a boil.
Cover. Reduce heat
and
simmer
hours.
Stir
occasionally. Remove bone.
Cut off meat and dice.
Return meat to soup; add celery and carrots.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven barbecue chicken and cheese biscuits
directions: Dip chicken in barbecue sauce.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°. Drain off some liquid, leaving some in pan.
Pour more sauce over chicken, if desired.
Pile chicken in one end of pan.
Place biscuits, separated, in pan in the drippings next to the chicken. Top biscuits with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until biscuits brown.

title: top ramen nappa salad
directions: Place noodles in pan (such as a pizza pan).
Sprinkle with almonds, sesame seed and noodles seasoning.
Place margarine in center.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°, stirring often until lightly browned.
Let cool.
Add cabbage and onions.

title: brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts. Bake in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: In medium bowl,
stir first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients;
toss to coat well.
Cover;
chill. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, beat together the margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the lemon extract.
Sift the flour and salt together, then mix into the wet ingredients.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let the cake cool in the pan, then turn out onto a plate.
Serves 12.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, put 1 heaping tablespoonful into a cup and add boiling water.
This dry mix makes an excellent gift when placed in a decorative Christmas tin.

title: maggie and jiggs casserole
directions: Cook cabbage. Make white sauce of remaining ingredients. Put corned beef in casserole with cabbage. Cover with white
sauce. Top with 4 slices bread, cubed and dipped in 2 Tbsp butter, and 6 cheese slices. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small saucepan, combine margarine, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Do not overbake.
While warm, ice with buttercream icing.

title: poor mary lobster
directions: Bring water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Drop in fish and simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Put melted butter in serving dish.
Remove fish with slotted spoon and add fish in single layer.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Spoon butter over and put in broiler 3 to 5-inches from flame.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli 10 minutes in 1 cup water.
Drain well.
Put cooked broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, butter, salt and pepper in pot.
Add enough milk (about 1 1/2 cups) to get the consistency you like.
Let simmer for 10 minutes; stir often! Serve in bowls with shredded Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika and Parmesan.
Put in 2 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix in blender, then pour into chilled 4-quart ice cream freezer container.
Add regular milk to fill line on can.
Follow directions on your ice cream maker and enjoy.

title: deluxe blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice; set aside.
In small bowl, blend pumpkin, milk.
In large mixer bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Alternately add flour and pumpkin mixtures to shortening mixture; beat well after each addition. Combine blueberries and 1 Tbsp. flour.
Gently stir blueberries into batter and spoon into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place slices on paper towels and sprinkle both sides with salt.
Cover with paper towels and weight down with a cutting board for 30 minutes to absorb excess moisture; pat dry.
Beat eggs well and set aside.
In separate bowl, mix flour, Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Place bread crumbs in separate bowl.

title: orange and pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in well-greased and floured cake pan, 3 layers or 2 oblong pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool layers completely.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Spread on party rye bread or crackers

title: your choice fried chicken
directions: Mix one part prepared yellow mustard to two parts water. Blend with whip or fork. To two cups of the flour, add all the ingredients. Blend well. Dip cleaned chicken pieces in mustard and water mixture. Roll dipped pieces in seasoned flour and pan or deep-fry for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: endive salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Drain
pineapple
tidbits;
reserve
tablespoons
of juice to
use
later.
Mix
together sugar and flour;
stir in juice. It will make a thick paste.
Mix cheese real well into the paste. Add pineapple and mix real good.
Put in a greased 1 quart Corning
pan.
Put cracker crumbs and a little butter on top. Bake
to
30 minutes at 350°.
Needs to bubble in the middle. Works better in a flat dish.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cut eggplant into small pieces after slicing.
Sprinkle with salt.
Allow eggplant to stand for 30 minutes, then rinse and pat dry on paper towels.
Heat the oil in a large skillet. Saute onions and	garlic	for 2 minutes.	Add green pepper and cook
for 2 minutes.	Add eggplant and cook over high heat for 3
minutes, stirring
constantly.
Add	zucchini and continue stirring for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, thyme and bay
leaf. Simmer,
uncovered,
for
40 minutes until all the vegetables are
tender.
Remove
bay	leaf*.	Garnish
with parsley and serve hot.	Serves 8.

title: oven chop suey
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 10 minutes, sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole(microwave)
directions: Cut cheese into chunks.
Place in microwave safe 1 quart casserole dish with 1/4 cup butter.
Microwave at Medium-high power for about 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir every 1 1/2 minutes. Add vegetables to casserole and mix.
Melt remaining butter in a bowl at High power for 30 seconds.
Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle buttered crumbs over vegetables in casserole.
Microwave at Medium-high power, uncovered, for about 10 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before serving. Serves 4.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon; add to the first mixture.
Add enough more flour so that dough doesn't stick to fingers.
Roll out 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with large cutter.
Crease with fork; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (8 to 10 minutes).

title: no bake cherry cheese squares
directions: In a medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; mix well.
Press firmly to bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill crust.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Blend together all of the ingredients.
Sprinkle the croutons on top of salad as you serve it.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: May add minced garlic, salt and pepper to taste and/or other colored bell peppers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 10 in. Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a small bowl, beat pumpkin, oil, juice, eggs and vanilla.
Stir pumpkin mixture into flour mixture until well combined.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tested in center comes out clean.
Turn out of pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mexican eggplant casserole
directions: Cut unpeeled eggplant into 1/2-inch slices and brush both sides with oil.
Arrange on a rimmed baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, in a 450° oven until soft, about 20 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Beat eggs, half and half and flour until smooth.
Split and rinse chilies (drain).
Mix cheeses; save 1/2 cup for top. Alternate layers in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pancake or waffle mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Either fry in a skillet or in a waffle iron.
Recipe works good for both.
Brown on both sides and butter.
Eat with gravy or with your favorite syrup.

title: *chocolate syrup pound cake*
directions: Put sugar, flour, Crisco, vanilla, eggs, margarine, baking powder and milk into mixing bowl; mix well.
Add chocolate syrup. Start baking in cold oven set at 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 15 to 20.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: In large bowl, mix together the oats, peanuts and peanut butter; set aside.
In kettle, mix sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine, salt and vanilla.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Pour over oatmeal mixture.
Blend well.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°; bake for 45 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: veal with olive sauce
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; dip in flour.
Slowly brown chops on both sides in hot fat; remove chops.
Blend the 2 tablespoons flour into fat.
Add salt, paprika, onion and lemon juice.
Add water.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Return chops to skillet.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes. Add olives; cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat oil, eggs and vanilla. Add all others. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 muffins.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients and add butter.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 325° until apples are tender.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.
Cool.

title: j. j. and j. sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and put in a large pizza pan.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: freezer corn
directions: Husk corn and cut from cob.
Cook all ingredients 5 minutes after you see the first sign of boiling.
Put into freezer containers.
If any juice is left in the pan, pour it evenly into each container.

title: super bowl 3 bean hot dish
directions: Cook meats, onion, salt and pepper until meat is lightly browned.
In large baking dish or crock-pot, add meat mixture and all beans.
Mix brown sugar, salt, ketchup and dry mustard and add to meat-bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or crock-pot it.

title: red raspberry topping
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a blender and whip until smooth.
Fold in the frozen raspberries very carefully.
Store in refrigerator and it lasts a long time.
Serve over pound cake, angel food cake or ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Blend all ingredients with hands in a large container.
Form ball and roll in parsley flakes and nuts, if desired.

title: honey chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in a large shallow baking pan in a single layer.
Sprinkle flavor enhancer, salt and pepper onto chicken; let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir together corn oil, honey and soy sauce; drizzle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 1 hour, basting frequently.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cut 1/2 stick butter or margarine and cheese in small bits. Add to broccoli in a greased casserole.
Crush 1/4 pound crackers with 1/2 stick melted butter or margarine and place on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: granny crumley's teacakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs with self-rising flour, adding flour until you have a stiff dough that leaves the bowl without sticking.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Knead down and roll into small balls.
Flatten and bake at 300° until brown.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef, sausage and onion.
Add salt, pepper, parsley flakes, garlic salt and tomato paste. Simmer slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While this cooks, combine water, noodles and butter.
Boil until done (25 minutes).
Drain.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and line bottom of dish with noodles.
Layer sauce, layer cottage cheese (large size) and layer Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with layer Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be made 2 hours prior to baking and refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Melt butter with garlic powder in nonstick pan and brown chicken in it.
Puree tomatoes and add Italian seasoning and pepper.
Put chicken in a baking dish and pour tomato sauce over. Put 1 slice of cheese over each chicken breast and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix nonfat cream cheese with marshmallow cream until smooth.
Serve with sliced apples, sliced bananas, chunk pineapple, drained, and mandarin orange slices, drained.

title: rotini salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar and spices in a saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes; cool.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in food processor.
Mix with cream cheese and seasonings (to taste).
Add sour cream.
Spread in flat baking dish.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.
This is also good cold with crackers.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased casserole with 1/2 bread and 1/2 cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and repeat layer.
Dot with butter. Beat eggs and milk together; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place casserole in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange marmalade
directions: First Day:
Wash and slice very thin the oranges and lemons. Remove seeds and cores.
Measure fruit.
For each cup of fruit, add 3 cups cold water.
Let stand, covered, at room temperature for 24 hours.

title: baked beef steak
directions: Pound flour into steaks on both sides.

title: orange french toast
directions: Combine eggs and orange juice.
Dip bread into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Fry on both sides in butter until brown.
Add additional butter each time more bread is added.
Serve with butter and warm maple syrup.
Great for company!
Serves about 5.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain well.
In a bowl, mix enchilada sauce, chicken soup and mushroom soup together with meat.
In casserole dish, put layer of Doritos.
Spoon in beef mixture.
Then sprinkle layer of cheese and then another of each.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; put in large bowl.
Add vanilla pudding; mix.
Add 2 tablespoons sour cream and 3 tablespoons Cool Whip; mix.
May add more sour cream and Cool Whip if needed.
Fill pie crust and chill.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In a bowl, stir together cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper and sour cream; set aside.
Prepare and boil quartered potatoes; drain.
Using an electric mixer or a potato masher, beat hot potatoes until they're in fine lumps.
Add sour cream mixture and continue beating until smooth.
Spoon potatoes into a well-buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
If made ahead, cover and refrigerate until the next day.
Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 25 minutes (50 minutes if refrigerated).
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes more, until top is golden brown.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: potato hot rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add shortening and mashed potatoes.
Mix with spoon and then with hands.
Add flour.
Make into rolls and bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
May be stored in refrigerator for 3 or 4 days in airtight container.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9x13-inch pan; sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan. Combine strawberries and dry jello. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Blend at low speed till moist. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour over marshmallows in pan. Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.

title: low cholesterol frosting with strawberries
directions: Combine sugar, egg white, salt, vanilla and strawberries in the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Beat on high speed for about 10 minutes or longer, until very thick and stiff.
Do not underbeat.
Use to frost your favorite cake about 30 minutes before serving.
Frosting can be refrigerated for two days.
(I use it on angel food.)

title: cheesy beans
directions: Melt butter in saucepan;
blend
in flour and add milk. Cook with constant
stirring
until
sauce boils and thickens. Season; add cheese and stir vigorously until melted.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add nuts and zucchini.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured cake pans or 20 x 14 1/2-inch cookie sheet.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, celery, green pepper, onion and pimento. Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in a pan.
Bring to a good, rolling boil.
Pour over vegetables and let set for 24 hours or at least overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place dry strawberries in pie crust.
Mix together in pan the sugar, water and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in strawberry jello.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate several
hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: meat ball stew and dumplings
directions: Add ingredients to
meat
balls.
Stir	gently;
cover. Bring to a boil.	Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Place Veg-All and water chestnuts in baking dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of celery soup and cheese.
Pour over vegetables. Combine Ritz crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Saute onion until delicately colored in olive oil, then remove.
Add the chicken pieces and brown on all sides.
Add wine, cloves, thyme, bay leaf, parsley, chicken stock and tomatoes. Cover the pot and simmer about 1 hour, until tender.
When meat is done, remove it to a platter.
Strain the sauce and reduce it about 5 minutes and season to taste.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower and onion; toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: In large skillet break up the ground beef.
Let beef get brown. Add tomato juice, then add tomato paste.
Add chili powder, garlic salt, sugar, oregano and minced onions.
Cover and bring to a boil. Cook spaghetti noodles.
Serve noodles with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, put 1/2 tube crushed Ritz crackers.
Add can of drained asparagus.
Mix soup with milk and add pimento.
Pour over asparagus.
Top with grated cheese and 1/2 tube crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: asparagus surprise
directions: Layer asparagus with juice, soup, chestnuts, crackers and cheese.
Pour melted butter over and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat and add next four ingredients.
Cover and simmer forty minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in 8 x 11-inch baking dish; cover with one-third of the sauce.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese, then half the cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes; cut in squares. Serves six.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone.
Cut into pieces.
Put in skillet with onion and cook onion.
Mix in 3/4 can soup.
Mix rest of soup with sour cream in bowl; spoon chicken mix in to enchiladas and roll.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with sour cream mix, then top with cheese.
Place in a 350° oven and melt cheese.

title: company strata
directions: From 12 slices white bread, cut 12 doughnuts and holes.
You will have nicer edges if you freeze the bread before cutting.
Fit the scraps of bread (top crusts removed) in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese slices, broccoli that has been cooked and drained, and ham over bread.
Arrange doughnuts and holes on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and dry mustard; pour over bread.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
For a pretty finish, sprinkle with shredded cheese last 5 minutes of baking.

title: frozen lemon cream
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs; place half of them in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Grate lemon rind.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender. Fry bacon until crisp and drain. Saute celery, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in bacon drippings. Add soup and mushroom juice plus 1/2 can water or chicken broth. Stir in cubed cheese. Add spaghetti and chicken which has been cut into pieces. Mix and put into casserole dish. Sprinkle with bacon crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly. Freezes well for later use.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Place in tube pan. Combine 1 cup sugar and margarine. Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak dry beans in water to cover overnight.
Drain and rinse beans.
Cover beans in fresh water and cook 1 hour or until tender.
Drain cooking water and rinse beans again.
Place beans in oven casserole.
Cook onions and garlic just to transparent. Place onion, garlic, catsup, mustard, sweetener, salt, pepper and turkey meat in casserole.
Water in small amounts may need to be added to prevent the ingredients becoming too dry.
Cook in slow oven (275° to 300°) for 4 to 5 hours.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut chicken for fricassee; simmer until tender.
Add spinach and cream of coconut.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add salt to taste.

title: calico beans
directions: Stir gently; put bacon on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 20.

title: easy pork chops and rice
directions: Combine the beef broth, green pepper, onion and rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with pork chops.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°, covered.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease casserole
and put boned chicken in bottom.
Mix soup and broth
and pour over chicken.
Cut up boiled eggs and put over this.
Mix
flour,
milk
and
margarine.	Pour over chicken and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine, sugars, vanilla, and eggs until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt, and baking soda. Mix into creamed mixture.
May have to use hands, because the dough is quite stiff.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Put in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: parmesan fish fillets
directions: Place fillets in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread evenly over fillets.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: hungarian mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Salt lightly.
Add mushrooms, dill, 1/2 cup stock, soy sauce and paprika.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Keeps very well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until all water evaporates.
Mix flour, milk, eggs, butter, salt, sugar and cheese.
Stir into squash mixture.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
You can add bread crumbs on top if you wish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and sugar.
Add cranberries which have been boiled until soft and drained.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serves 12.

title: beef tacos
directions: In skillet over high heat, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until all pan juices evaporated and meat is well browned, stirring frequently.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Stir green chilies, roasted red peppers, chili sauce, sugar and salt into mixture; over medium heat, heat through.
To serve, spoon meat mixture into warm bowl.
Arrange shredded cheese, chopped tomatoes and sliced lettuce in separate bowls for taco accompaniments.
Let each person spoon some beef mixture into a taco shell, then top with taco accompaniments and taco sauce.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl combine dry ingredients and add milk.
Mix well.
Pour over butter; spread to cover bottom of pan.
Spoon pie filling over top of batter.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecups
directions: Separate biscuit dough into 12 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle each with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: the chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into cream mixture.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during cooking and flatten during cooking.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mexican doritos
directions: Brown beef with onions.
Drain and add tomatoes, mushroom and chicken soup and jalapenos.
Crush Doritos while they are still in the bag.
Layer the Doritos, sauce mixture and cheese:
1 layer Doritos, 1 layer of sauce mixture and 1 layer of Cheddar cheese. End with cheese on top after repeating layers.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cook pudding in milk according to package directions.
Stir in dry cake mix, stirring only until mix is moistened.
Do not overstir.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bea brake's ambassador praline pie
directions: Bake the pie shell for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour mixture of melted butter, brown sugar and pecans into the pie shell.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Make vanilla pudding according to package directions for pie filling. Pour the pudding over top of pecan mixture; reserve one cup of the pie filling and allow to cool.
Add half of the Cool Whip to the cup of reserved pie filling and stir together.
Add this to the filling already inside the pie.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Add the remaining Cool Whip on top of the pie and garnish with whole pecan halves.
Chill thoroughly and keep cold until serving.
A wonderful treat for yourself and your guests!

title: cherry-nut dessert
directions: Mix together pie filling and pineapple and spread it on loaf cake pan (no greasing).
Sprinkle dry cake mix on this.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: salsa dip(good)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
May add some hot pepper or Tabasco for a hot taste.

title: polish meatballs(for large group)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and use bread crumbs to make nice meatballs.
Roll in bread crumbs and saute in oil until well browned.
Add water to meatballs and chicken cubes.
Simmer 3 hours at 275°.
Add mushroom soup to make gravy.
Color with Kitchen Bouquet.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth and chill.
As you roll into small balls, roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake 6 to 12 minutes in 370° oven.
Cookies will crack on top.

title: 7-up pineapple cream salad
directions: Combine beverage (7-Up) and marshmallows in top of double boiler; heat over boiling water until marshmallows are melted. Pour over lime gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add hot mixture slowly to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice, crushed pineapple and walnuts.
Chill until partially set and thick.
Fold in whipped cream; blend thoroughly.
Pour into an oiled 2-quart mold or dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter; add sifted dry ingredients.
Mold a teaspoon of dough around each olive.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 48 puffs.

title: cake pan preparation mixture
directions: Place in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Put back in a container with secure lid.
This can be kept in your cabinet.

title: auntie's cutout cookies
directions: Cream 1 1/2 packages cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll and cut out into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Combine remaining cream cheese, milk and rind, mixing until well blended.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Tint frosting, if desired.
Frost cookies and decorate.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let mixture soak for 3 hours.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and juice; add cheese and pineapple.
Put into 1-quart casserole; cover with combined margarine and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add milk and cocoa.
Blend well.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick. Add egg yolks and mix well.
Cook 1 minute.
Blend in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Alternate layers of peas, asparagus, mushroom soup and cracker crumbs until all ingredients are used.

title: meema's ham loaf
directions: Grind together the following:
smoked ham and lean pork.
Add eggs and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix with 1 cup milk to form a loaf.
Boil together brown sugar, water, vinegar and dry mustard. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and cold pack in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple well.
Heat juice hot to dissolve jello.
Put in freezer and let thicken, then stir in Coke.
Put back in freezer until thick.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and pecans along with cream cheese.
Pour into mold and let congeal. Refrigerate.

title: 3 alarm chili
directions: Add the chopped onion to hamburger until softened.
Add all ingredients; cook slowly, not to burn tomatoes or spices.
When flavors have combined, enjoy.

title: fruit-topped pudding pie
directions: Combine pie filing mix with milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool cooked pudding 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Cut pie into 6 to 8 wedges and top each alternately with fresh fruit.

title: hot lemonade
directions: Juice several lemons, then scrub the peel well. Slice it thinly and add to the juice. Cover all with plenty of boiling water. Cover and steep until cool. For added benefit, add several slices of ginger root before covering with water. Strain off liquid. Add honey and additional water to taste. Drink hot. (This is great for sore throats.)

title: peanut butter bites
directions: Mix all ingredients except almond bark together well.
Roll into finger size rolls and let cool.
Melt chocolate flavored almond bark in a double boiler and dip balls, one at a time, use a fork.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well after each addition.
Batter should be smooth.
Pour into prepared baking pan. If using Bundt or tube pan, bake for one hour.
Cool on rack; unmold.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon tortillas
directions: Heat tortillas in frying pan or on flat grill, whatever you cook pancakes on, until hot and crisp. Spread with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and cut with pizza cutter into triangles.
Kids will love them!

title: candy cake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
first cake cubes, then Cool Whip mixture, then candy.
Repeat.

title: rissoto
directions: Have quite a bit of broth ready on the side.
In thick pan, saute onion, then put sauce in it.
Put your rice in the pan and just keep stirring.
As it thickens, you pour broth in it so that it doesn't burn.
Just keep stirring as you put in the broth.
It takes about an hour to cook.
It's very good.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add 1 pound cooked and drained noodles to mixture.
Place in large baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit, add pecans, raisins and lemon extract.
Pour flour over nuts and fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks. Pour all of this into fruit.
Beat egg whites good.
Fold egg whites in last.
Cook for 3 hours at 250°.

title: diabetic applesauce cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream oleo until fluffy. Beat egg and sugar. Add oleo and blend. Sift dry ingredients. Add to oleo mixture alternately with applesauce. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Bake 20 minutes. Makes 12 cupcakes.

title: caramels
directions: Boil slowly until 248 degrees.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool.
Cut and wrap.

title: peggy's barbecue chicken
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add sauce. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: asparagus, pea and soup casserole
directions: Place in casserole asparagus, then peas, next soup.
Sprinkle a good layer of shredded cheese on soup and top with bread crumbs that have been soaked in butter. Bake until heated through at 350°.

title: aunt della's make ahead pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly. Knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Pinch off enough for each crust.
Roll into individual balls and put into ziploc freezer bags. Use or Freeze.
Great crusts.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and oil all at once.
Stir just until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Combine Shortening and butter.
Add confectionary sugar and vanilla.
Blend til fluffy.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix together until smooth.
Press batter into a 9 x 12 inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 - 20 minutes, until golden in color.
Cool well.

title: super bowl barbecued roast
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker overnight or lowest oven setting.
In the morning, cut up meat. Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 more cup ketchup.
It's ready anytime you are.
Serve on hamburger buns and enjoy!

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need mini foil liners.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Brown onions in oil; add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Cut up franks and place in glass dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "miss" lynette's favorite shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix corn, beans, bell pepper, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; mix well.
Divide into 4 cheese balls; roll in chili powder or chopped nuts.
I prefer both.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: oriental turkey(serves 4)
directions: Coat preheated skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Add turkey slices and cook until both sides are brown.
Place turkey on platter and cover to keep warm.
Place green peppers, celery and green onions in same skillet; cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add diced tomatoes.
Dissolve tomato soup in water, then pour over vegetables.
Add seasonings.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over turkey.

title: company chicken with savory rice
directions: Shake thawed chicken parts in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Allow to stand 10 minutes or so to absorb flour.
Brown thoroughly on all sides in hot shortening.
Place browned pieces in a large casserole.
Stir cream of chicken soup into the pan in which the chicken was browned in order to pick up drippings.
Use part or all as desired. Add curry and mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken. Cover and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve chicken with rice steamed in consomme or French onion soup.
Prepare 1 1/3 cups quick cooking rice as directed on package except substitute canned consomme or onion soup for the water.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all together; add topping of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Make in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Makes 9 good squares.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in serving pieces.
Combine rest of ingredients for sauce, except onions.
Place a layer of ribs in roasting pan. Slice one onion over them and cover with half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover pan and bake at 325° for two hours.
Uncover last half hour.

title: hot clam and cheese dip(appetizer)
directions: Simmer clams, juice and lemon juice in small saucepan for 15 minutes.
Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, oregano and Tabasco sauce in butter.
Add breadcrumbs to clams and sauce.
Mix in vegetables.
Spray small casserole dish with Pam.
Place 1/2 mixture in dish and cover with half the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Ritz, Triscuits or any plain cracker.

title: baked meat loaf
directions: Saute onions and pepper in garlic and butter for 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaves.
Rub top loaves with cooking oil (prevents cracks).
Cover with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan and add flour.
Mix well and add mushroom soup.
Add mushrooms.
Set aside, but keep warm.
Buy the cut of chicken preferred.

Boil; remove from bone, cut up and set aside. Take 2 1/2 cups of the broth from the chicken and cook the rice by using directions on package using broth instead of water. Layer the mushroom mixture, chicken and the wild rice in a casserole dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake long enough to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: fresh vegetable nicoise
directions: In microwave in a 2-quart casserole, cook green beans in 1/4 cup water, covered, on High 4 to 6 minutes or until slightly softened.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain and stir in onion, garlic and oil; cook, covered, 3 minutes.
Stir in yellow pepper and cook, covered, 2 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Add tomato; cook, uncovered, 1 minute.
Stir in olives and remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cracker roca
directions: Line crackers on cookie sheet, approximately 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bring margarine and sugar to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over pan of crackers.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°. Remove from oven and turn oven off.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Return to oven to melt chocolate.
Spread chocolate and sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Let cool.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten egg whites.
Plop on foil. Place in preheated 350° oven. Turn off immediately.
Let stay in oven for hours, or even overnight.

title: dirt cups
directions: In a blender or food processor, crush Oreos and set aside. Using a mixer, cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl, combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Add cream cheese mixture to pudding mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator.
Put 2 cups crushed potato chips on top and bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Slightly cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice and saute onion in margarine.
Combine in casserole: cooked broccoli, rice, onion, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Top with slivered almonds before baking.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the graham cracker crumbs.
Pat down and bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add the Hershey bars on top evenly.
When they are melted, spread.
Cut into squares.

title: pie crust
directions: Work flour, crisco, and salt together into pea stage. Mix water and brown sugar. Let set. Add to flour mixture and mix well. Tear off enough for 1 crust (8 oz.) and freeze.

title: broccoli cheese quiche
directions: Semi cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Cube cheeses.
In bottom of pie shells, arrange broccoli and cheeses. Mix eggs and cream until foamy.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!
Makes 2 quiches.

title: spicy rice nacho platter
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute onion and green pepper over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in water, rice, Spanish sauce and cumin.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and chilies until cheese is melted. Cool slightly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and beat in the 4 eggs, one at a time. Bake in a greased pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy dip
directions: Microwave together until cheese melts enough to blend easily with the salsa.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chimichangas
directions: Completely defrost chuck roast.
Cook in crock-pot or slow cooker on low until tender and shreds easily with a fork.
For a bit of extra flavor, you may want to season the water you cook the roast in with garlic powder and black pepper.
After meat is tender, drain, remove fat and put back in crock-pot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables 3/4 of cook time.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Lightly butter 2-quart casserole.
Lay cauliflower in bottom of dish; cover with 1/3 sauce.
Lay peas and carrots on top of sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°. Enjoy!
Serves 10.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, depending on oven.
Cool 10 minutes and remove.

title: creamy cajun chicken with pasta bourbon street style(4 servings)
directions: Cook garlic
in
butter in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat
for
seconds.
Stir in chicken and seasoning mix.
Cook until
lightly
browned, about 3 minutes.
Stir in green onions. Cook 1
minute more.
Add cream.
Increase heat to high and boil until
slightly
thickened, about 2 minutes. Combine chicken mixture, pasta and parsley in serving bowl and pass the Parmesan.

title: chicken (tuna) noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water, drain.
Melt margarine, add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, stir in next 6 ingredients.
Add chicken and noodles.
Put in casserole, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Can use one 7-ounce can of tuna instead of chicken.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bone.
Prepare cornbread according to directions on box.
Boil eggs.
Crumble cornbread and put into greased baking dish.
Pour chicken broth over cornbread to make moist.
Place chicken over the top of cornbread.
Put both cans of cream of chicken soup on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: In large deep kettle (will froth high), combine sugar, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes until a little mixture in cold water forms a very soft ball or to 210° on candy thermometer, being sure to stir frequently and to scrape bottom and side of kettle.
Remove from heat and drop in the butter.
Stand by while mixing cools slightly (just a minute or two).
Then, with a spoon, beat until thickened and creamy (losing its gloss).
Immediately drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper, aluminum foil or cookie sheet.
Dot with pecans.

title: summer garden soup
directions: Saute the green peppers in the oil 5 to 10 minutes; do not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, hot seasoning and the chicken broth. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add milk only to heat, do not boil. Place cheese in bottom of soup bowl.
Pour soup on cheese and top with croutons.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add oil and mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with evaporated milk.
Add poppy seed and nuts.
Pour into well-greased pans (2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Freezes well and is delicious toasted.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, and broth in a soup pot. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Cool.
Add a teaspoon of chicken bouillon granules, if necessary.
Place soup in a blender, puree.
Pour the pureed soup back into the soup pot, add milk and heat.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.
Calories 129, fat 1.5 grams.

title: fruit punch
directions: Turn juices into 6-quart bowl. Stir in ice water and ginger ale.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in a tightly sealed jar. Use 1 1/2 teaspoonfuls in a teacup of hot water or 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a mug.

title: country club eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube 7 slices bread and line pan. Spread cheese over bread, then meat.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over all.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Cube 2 slices bread and set on top until well soaked. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: french cocoa
directions: Combine chocolate, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Gradually add milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in orange juice.
Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with orange rind.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocado, add lemon juice and salt.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon and ground beef. Mix all ingredients with beans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla together.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Note:
Flour and baking soda should be sifted together.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients with 1/2 stick melted butter. Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes with 1/2 stick melted butter and crumble on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix eggs, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix salmon, 1/2 of cracker crumbs and 1/2 of egg mixture with seasoning.
Form into egg shaped lumps.
Dip into remaining egg mixture; roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot grease and brown.
Drain on brown paper.

title: sparkle strawberry cake
directions: Beat by hand until mixed well (does not take long).
Pour into greased Pyrex rectangle dish, approximately 6 1/2 x 11-inch size. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers, then add a layer of pudding.
Repeat with graham crackers and pudding again.
Top with graham crackers, then spread chocolate frosting on top.

title: ginger peach melba
directions: Soften ice cream; blend in candied ginger. Pack in 6-cup mold; cover and freeze several hours until firm. Mash raspberries in saucepan; add jelly. Bring to boil; blend cornstarch and water, then stir into raspberries mixture. Cook, stirring constantly until thick and clear. Strain sauce. Cool and chill.
At serving time, unmold ice cream on plate. Arrange peaches (blueberries if you want) over ice cream. Spoon sauce over fruit and ice cream. Serve with thin ginger cookies are good with this.

title: cole slaw with a kick
directions: Place all ingredients, except cabbage, into a mixing bowl and beat well with a wooden spoon.
Pour over cabbage and mix thoroughly.

title: duxbury baked scallops
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, mix in bread crumbs and crushed Ritz crackers.
Put half of crumb mixture in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Put scallops on top, then rest of crumb mixture.
Pour cream over all, add a few extra pats of butter and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, layer Doritos, then chicken and then chopped onion.
Mix all soups in saucepan; heat to a boil. Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in oven for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: yum yum chicken dish
directions: In shallow baking pan.
Place dried beef on bottom.
Wrap each chicken breast in a slice of bacon and place on top of dried beef. Mix undiluted soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Serve over rice.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Let ice cream soften.
Stir in peanut butter.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil, eggs and frozen strawberries and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Blend sugar, drained strawberries and butter until creamy.
If icing is too thin, add a little sugar.
Spread icing on cake after it is completely cooled.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil 4 or 5 sweet potatoes until tender. Peel and cut in half. Lay in casserole dish. Mix all ingredients and let come to a boil. Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: pecan drops
directions: In
a
bowl,
beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on	medium	to
high
speed
about	30 seconds or until softened. Add
powdered
sugar, about half of the flour, half of
the
milk and
the
vanilla to the margarine.
Beat until thoroughly combined,
scraping
sides	of
bowl occasionally. Then
beat
or stir
in
remaining
flour	and milk.
Stir in chopped
pecans. Drop
dough from a rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart	on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
If desired, lightly press a pecan half in center of each cookie. Bake
in
oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are slightly golden.
Remove
cookies
and
cool
on a wire rack. Makes about 48.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine or butter and milk on stove.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix together.
Spoon onto wax paper; let cool.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Pour over crust and top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Refrigerate and serve cold; cut in small squares.

title: pumpkin cake dessert
directions: Mix and put into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 11 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Top with topping.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into prepared graham cracker crust and freeze (about 1/2 day).

title: strawberry pecan bread
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat until well combined.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Beat until well blended (batter should be thick).
Stir in partially thawed, undrained berries and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Freezes well.
I usually double recipe.
This will make 4 loaves when doubled.

title: tangy cranberry sauce meatballs
directions: Combine in a saucepan and heat, stirring occasionally.
Add meatballs to sauce and heat through.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Butter a small casserole and line the bottom and sides with small squares of buttered bread.
Cut off the crusts.
Make a custard of the ingredients.
Mix and pour over the bread. Sprinkle ground cinnamon or nutmeg, whichever preferred, over top. Raisins may be added if you wish.
Place casserole in pan of boiling water and bake at 350° for one hour (or until a sliver knife comes out clean).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and oil.
Beat in 2 eggs; sift and stir in salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix together well.
Chill dough.
Roll in balls.
Place on a cookie sheet (unbuttered).
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chilli
directions: Cook onion and add them to meat and cook.
Mix flour, salt and chili powder together.
When meat is done, add the flour, salt and chili powder together.
Add tomato juice or water.
