title: daiquiri dessert
directions: Blend berries, rum and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Beat eggs. Add onion, cheese and soup.
Add broccoli, mayonnaise and 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Work flour mixture into ingredients, adding more flour, if needed, to make dough the proper consistency.
Chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake on slightly greased cookie sheet in 375° oven for about 10 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: nutty candy bar pie
directions: In the top of a double boiler melt candy bars, peanut butter and half and half.
Remove from heat and fold in whipped cream. Pour into crust.
Freeze for 4 to 6 hours.
If desired, drizzle with chocolate syrup before freezing.

title: peggy's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour until creamy.
Stir in broth and cream; cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add sherry, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour in greased 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covering for the first 40 minutes.

title: hot, sour and sweet pickles
directions: Pour liquid off dill pickles.
After draining, cut pickles in quarters lengthwise and then chop.
Pour sugar over pickles.
Add Tabasco sauce and clove of garlic.
Mix well.
Let stand for a day or more in refrigerator.
Separate into small jars.
It makes enough to give as gifts to all your friends.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Let dough rise until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Roll loaves together into one 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cook meat; drain well.
Place 3/4 of the meat down one half of the dough. Spread 1/4 cup of pizza sauce over the meat.
Add green pepper and onion.
Add the rest of the meat and pepperoni.
Sprinkle the spices over the top.
Drizzle the remaining pizza sauce on top. Place the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Fold the empty side of dough over the filling.
Seal edges well.
Spray a large cookie sheet with Pam.
Place loaf on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice into 1-inch slices and serve warm.

title: orange roughy with basil blend
directions: In a small bowl, stir together margarine and basil leaves. Place fillets on greased broiler pan.
Spread one side of fillets with half of margarine mixture.
Broil 5 to 8 inches away from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn fillets over and top with remaining margarine mixture and lemon slices.
Continue broiling for 5 to 6 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Yields 4 servings.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Put in oven immediately and bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.
Chill.

title: peach cobbler 2
directions: Mix first four ingredients until smooth.
Place in a large casserole bowl and then put sliced peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour 1/2 quart berries in baked pie shell.
Mash other half of berries; add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook slowly until clear. Stirring constantly, pour over berries in pie shell.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: turkey a la king
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion. Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt and pepper.
Blend in milk, water and bouillon granules.
Cook and stir over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in turkey, mushrooms, peas and pimiento.
Continue cooking for about 5 minutes or until hot and peas are tender.
Serve over toast points or in patty shells.
Top with almonds.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cook onion and sausage balls in skillet until onion is tender and sausage is lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, cover, reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add peas, cover, let simmer another 5 to 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have butter, cream cheese and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese thoroughly (about 10 minutes).
Add sugar. Beat another 10 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.
Add eggs and beat another 10 minutes.
Add flavoring and salt.
Add flour gradually on slow speed.
Beat only until mixed well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Put into a cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not peek while baking!!!

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Brown meat.
Add 1 teaspoon minced onion, pinch of oregano and garlic powder.
Drain and cool.
Add Ricotta cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese to the meat.
Boil 12 strips of lasagna until soft.
Drain and add cold water.
Mix Ragu with tomato sauce. Spread 1/2 cup on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish (non-aluminum).

title: zippli(fry dough)
directions: Add yeast and sugar in warm water, then blend remaining ingredients
altogether.
Add water with the yeast.
Work batter good with hands.
Make rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix again with hands.
Then fry in hot oil.
Drop a teaspoon of batter in hot oil and fry until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: almond joys
directions: Mix all together (except the almonds).
Spoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Press on almonds and put into freezer overnight. Dip into chocolate.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Simmer broccoli in approximately 1 quart of salted hot water for a few seconds.
Add uncooked spaghetti and cook for 8 minutes. Drain and add remaining ingredients; toss together to mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Add rice and almonds.
Saute the chopped onion in small amount butter.
Add milk and cream of chicken soup.
Add 1/2 pound of cheese, chopped. Pour mixture into large greased casserole.
Add remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: small pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs and flour alternately. Mix about 5 minutes.
Add flavors.
Grease and flour pan.
Cook at 275° for 45 minutes and then turn oven up to 300° and cook until done.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Dissolve and chill Jell-O.
Beat milk and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Roll graham crackers.
Place half of cracker mixture into dish and pour mixture of Jell-O and milk over crumbs. Sprinkle other half on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: ravioli pasta salad
directions: Cook ravioli per directions.
Drain and let cool.
Add, green pepper and celery.
Mix together salad dressing and salad supreme.
Pour over ravioli and vegetables. Mix well and chill for about an hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs, flour, bananas and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine the above in 1-quart size dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease casserole dish. Combine rice, cheese, chicken, milk, onion, eggs, cilantro, butter and jalapeno in prepared casserole dish, stir well. Bake 45-50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Season with salt.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Brown celery and onions in margarine.
Mix all together. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients with melted butter until crumbly; set aside.
Place 2 cups or more apples in bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with half crumb mixture; repeat.
Drizzle orange juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate walnut torte
directions: Place oven rack in lower third of oven. Heat oven to 350°.

title: steak and noodles with mushroom sauce
directions: Slice steak up into cubes.
Season lightly with whatever seasonings you prefer.
Place in a baking dish.
Cover with foil, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix the two soups together and pour mixture over steak pieces.
Also add chopped onion and mushroom slices.
Bake for another hour.
Boil noodles approximately 20 minutes.
Drain.
Pour steak and mushroom sauce over noodles.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Melt margarine; mix in sugar. Stir in eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition. Stir 1 cup chips into the batter. Spread in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining chips and nuts. Bake 30 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and cut. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sandwich rollers
directions: Mix French onion dip and mayonnaise.
Spread over top of tortilla.
Layer thin sliced meat on that; sprinkle with cheese and peppers.
Roll up and slice into party sandwiches.
Many other items may be added instead of peppers (i.e. shredded lettuce, thinly sliced pickles or olives).
Chill and serve.

title: quiche
directions: Layer cheese, ham, bell pepper, mushrooms and olives in pie crust.
Beat eggs and cream until well mixed.
Pour over ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
I recommend you place on a cookie sheet.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toss cabbage, onion, pepper, pimento and sugar.
Bring to a boil remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss and tightly seal container.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low at least 4 hours.
Individual servings can be topped with grated cheese if desired.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: golden chicken
directions: Melt oleo/margarine in baking dish.
Add other ingredients. Roll chicken pieces in butter mixture.
Then lay chicken in mixture and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: hawaiian meat loaf
directions: Make meat loaf; top with an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: t.c.p. play dough
directions: Bring water to rapid boil.
Add remaining ingredients (premixed) except flour to boiling water and stir well (it will not dissolve).
Remove from stove.
Add in flour.
Stir, stir, stir until combined.
Knead when cool.

title: cranberry-cream gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and chill until thickened, but not firm.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: various ways to serve angel food cake
directions: Slice 1-inch layer from top of cake and put aside.
Scoop out center of bottom part of cake making a trench all around (save cake and serve in individual dishes with favorite pudding and whipped topping).
Fill trench with 1 of the following:
Ice cream, softened, mixed with fruit, chocolate Cool Whip and bananas, whipped cream and fruit and nuts, partially set fruited Jell-O; freeze cake with ice cream and refrigerate others.
Put top back on and top accordingly.

title: niki's apple raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease generously only bottoms of 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly (1 minute).
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Pour into pans.

title: pistachio-pineapple delight
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Add the mix with a wire whisk.
Beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Store in the refrigerator. Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Peel apples and slice in small bowl.
In large mixing bowl, put in oil, sugar and eggs and mix until creamy.
Stir in salt, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir well, then add flour a little at a time until mixed well.
Stir in sliced apples and pour into lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 2 small loaves.

title: country pie
directions: Mix well with fork all ingredients for crust and put in bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken broccoli delight
directions: Completely cook chicken in Miracle Whip about 8 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mrs. t's spaghetti sauce
directions: Put garlic, onions and green pepper in olive oil in large skillet.
Cook onions until golden.
Add and cook meat.
Skim off fat.
Then cook tomatoes.
Add paste, sugar and spices.
Use water or tomato sauce to thin.
Let sauce mellow for at least a day before serving over spaghetti.

title: oven stew beef supper
directions: Cut stew beef into bite size pieces and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch roasting pan.
Slice potato rounds to cover beef.
Slice onion rounds over potatoes.
Slice carrot rounds over onions. Dot with butter or margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add water; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: slush
directions: In large container that can be put in freezer, mix 1-1/2 cups sugar, 1 cup warm water to dissolve sugar, and add above 3 juices plus 6 cups water.
Mix well and add one fifth of vodka.
Put in freezer.
Make up several hours before use.
Will not completely freeze.
Fill glass 3/4 full with slush and top off with 7-Up or Sprite.
Makes large batch.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add bacon (chopped), ham, pepper, onions and 3 scrambled eggs.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons bacon grease for taste.
Do not add salt.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: Combine ham, onions and green pepper.
Place 1/3 cup mixture plus 3 tablespoons grated Cheddar cheese on each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine eggs, cream, flour, salt, garlic powder and Tabasco sauce and pour over tortillas.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 3 additional minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first three ingredients.
Pour in bowl and add flour, salt and sugar.
Beat well and add eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour batter into a greased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then add confectioners sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread frosting on warm cake.

title: pork roast
directions: Rub brown sugar into pork.
Place in deep roasting pan. Sprinkle well with salt and pepper.
Then add tomatoes, onion, Tabasco, catsup and water to the pan.
Baste often with the mixture while baking.
Roast in open roasting pan at 300° for 3 1/2 hours or until well done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork soup
directions: Soak
mushrooms
in
water; set aside.	Brown pork with garlic and
ebi in a 6-quart saucepan.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups of water,
a can of clams and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season with salt, pepper, shoyu and ajinomoto (optional).	Add
scallops and
onion;
simmer
for
5 minutes.
Add cabbage
which
has been
cut into 2-inch pieces.
Serve when cabbage is cooked. Makes 5 servings.

title: old country store coca cola cake
directions: In a saucepan bring Coca Cola, oil, margarine, and cocoa to a boil.
Mix together sugar, flour, and salt.
Pour in the boiling liquid and beat well.
Add the eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan.

title: french cream frosting
directions: Combine flour and milk. Cook until thick and cool.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and beat until light and fluffy.

title: tomato aspic mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold tomato juice.
Pour into hot tomato juice and dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 5-cup ring mold and chill until firm.
Unmold onto chilled serving plate and trim with lettuce.

title: bojangle biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well and form into biscuits.
Melt 1 stick of butter and spoon over biscuits before baking.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: turkey stuffing casserole
directions: Place margarine or butter in round 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Cover loosely and microwave on High until melted, 45 to 60 seconds.
Add stuffing and water; toss to coat stuffing.
Remove 1 cup stuffing.
Spread remaining mixture evenly in baking dish. Mix soup, peas, milk and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 3 minutes; stir.
Cover and microwave until hot and bubbly, 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Stir in chicken or turkey.
Spread mixture over stuffing in baking dish. Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove inner junk.
Place in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle insides with salt. Place "face down" on paper towel.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut orange slices into small pieces. Beat egg yolks.
Add brown sugar and vanilla into flour mixture. Beat egg whites stiff; stir into mixture.
Put into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar when hot.

title: soft shell tacos
directions: Brown the beef until done.
Drain grease off hamburger.
Add 1/4 cup of water, seasoning, beans and mix all together.
Mixture should not be too thick or too thin.
If it's too thick add more water.
Let simmer until warm meanwhile, get out another pan, put it on stove and warm the pan.
Place tortilla shells one at a time in the pan.
Warm the sides of the shells.
Take the shells and place it on a plate, and put the taco mixture on the shell.
Roll the shell up, repeat until you run out of meat or shells.
Add lettuce, cheese, onions, etc. if you like.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles in water until tender; drain and rinse with cold water. Add chopped boiled egg, vegetables and cheese. Moisten with Ranch dressing; salt and pepper to taste.

title: mocha sorbet
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa powder, coffee powder and 2 tablespoons of the water in a medium-size bowl.
Mix together to form a paste. Gradually stir in remaining water and coffee liqueur until well blended and smooth.

title: low calorie casserole
directions: Place chopped cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion and stir in rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put meat/rice mixture in casserole dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May add more water if casserole gets too dry.
199 calories per serving.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining flour and other dry ingredients, including yeast, in a large bowl. Stir margarine and water into dry mix.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make very thick batter. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Turn batter into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size, about 30 to 45 minutes. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per box instructions.
Make cake into 2 layers.
Split 2 layers to make 4 once baked.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut, setting 1 cup mixture aside.
Place mixture between all layers stacking cake.
Use mixture set aside for top of cake.

title: sweet-n-sour shrimp
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in oil until tender.
Sprinkle flour over mixture; stir rapidly to keep smooth.
Pour tomato juice over mixture; continue stirring until thickened a bit.
Add sugar, stirring constantly, then lemon juice and rind.
Reduce heat to warm and add shrimp.
Let set for an hour or so while flavors blend.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Makes 30 to 40 small cookies.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add lemon rind and nuts.

title: yoghurt chicken
directions: Melt butter in a deep lidded frying pan.
Add onions, peppercorns, cardamon and cinnamon.
Fry until onions are golden. Add ginger, garlic, chili powder, paprika and salt to taste.
Fry for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken pieces and fry until browned.
Gradually add the yoghurt, stirring constantly. Cover and cook gently for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
If stiff, add 2 tablespoons of honey, not milk or water.
Bake no more than 13 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs. Add oil to creamed mixture. Add dry ingredients. Stir in grated carrots and walnuts. Place batter in a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into meatballs.
Cover with 1 jar of spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Bake an additional 15 minutes uncovered.

title: no fail punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix salt, sesame oil, m.s.g., sugar and black pepper together. Add to chicken.
Mix flour, starch, baking powder, salad oil and water in blender.
Pour over chicken and fry.
When eating sweet and sour chicken you will need a cup of sweet and sour sauce.

title: dream cake
directions: While cake is still hot, poke holes in top and pour pineapple juice over hot cake.
Let cool.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip. Spread on cake. Add layer of coconut, layer of nuts and layer of chopped maraschino cherries. Refrigerate.

title: baked eggplant with meat stuffing
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise and cook in 2 quarts boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Pour off water, then scoop out eggplant pulp; chop up and save.
Leave a shell about 1/2-inch thick.
Saute chopped onion and pepper in butter for about 5 minutes, until onion is light yellow.
Add the meat and continue cooking until meat loses pink color.
Stir constantly; add chopped eggplant pulp, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove from stove and when cool, stir in beaten egg. Fill eggplant shells; place in lightly greased baking pan and add 2 tablespoons water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix thoroughly in order as listed, adding Coca-Cola very last. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door while baking!
Let cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: budget cake
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: easy grilled cheese
directions: Put the bread in the toaster, when it pops up put the cheese on it, then put it in the microwave for about 30 seconds.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender, drain and reserve 6 tablespoons water.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add carrots, water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and clear.
Add carrots and heat on low 5 minutes.
Stir in butter and serve.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: banana crush
directions: Mash bananas in blender.
Add all ingredients, except lemon-lime drink.
Put in containers and freeze.
Approximately 3 hours before serving, remove from freezer and let stand at room temperature.
Pour lemon-lime over crush and stir.
Should have a slush consistency.
If you use square quart containers to freeze, it takes 1 1/2 hours of thawing time out of the freezer to be of the right consistency.
Serves 50.

title: stew for a crowd(serves 25 people)
directions: Use an electric roaster.
Add cooking oil and preheat to 350°. While roaster is preheating, season meat with salt, pepper, paprika and a dash or two of garlic powder.
Add meat to roaster and sear on all sides.
After meat is seared, add beef bouillon, garlic powder, bay leaves, mustard seed and oregano.
Cook at medium heat 225° until meat is tender, but not falling apart.
Add tomato soup; bring to a boil.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add celery and green peppers.
Add salt over each addition of vegetables.
Use hot water for desired consistency during cooking.
Add potatoes and cook until all vegetables are done.
Reduce heat to 175°.
This will hold ready to serve.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Now stir in nuts, raisins and apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Makes 1 Bundt or 2 loaf size cakes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry drop cake
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and save.
In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, place blueberries in a layer on bottom.
Place pineapple on 2nd layer.
Add 1 unmixed yellow cake mix.
Add pineapple juice and butter on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake for 20 to 30 minutes until done.

title: veggie bars
directions: Veggies: broccoli, cauliflower, green peppers, onions, carrots.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream well the butter and sugar; add eggs, milk, bread crumbs and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Sprinkle sugar with nutmeg.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs and milk, salt and baking powder.
Gradually add flour, working into a stiff dough, but not tough.
Roll about about 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips about 4 inches long.
Drop into hot chicken broth and cook until done.
Add boned chicken, thickened with broth if desired.

title: serbian broccoli hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese and flour.
Cube margarine and cheese.
Mix well and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole.

title: quick tuna dip
directions: Mix one can of tuna (drained) with 1 container of French onion dip.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Better when chilled.

title: crunchy topped rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix together brown sugar, oil, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix together until well blended.
Add rhubarb and nuts.
Spoon into paper lined muffin tins, 2/3 full. Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over top of muffins.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can also be baked in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: anita's swedish apple cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter until fluffy.
Work in flour and salt. Pat into greased cookie sheet with edge.
Top with apple slices. Season with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mimosa cauliflower salad
directions: Leave the cauliflower head whole, but remove all green leaves. In a large pot, bring 2 cups of water to a boil and add lemon juice, salt and the cauliflower.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 20 minutes, until the cauliflower is just crisp.
Remove; drain and cool to lukewarm.

title: recipe for a home
directions: Cream friendship and thoughtfulness with a pinch of tenderness.
Mix lightly loyalty, faith, hope and charity.
Add gaiety, song and laughter.
Moisten with tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg then into bread crumbs.
Cook chicken in olive oil until done and well browned.
Pour spaghetti sauce into a 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce and put Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° or until cheese is melted and lightly brown.

title: no-fat cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, peel and slice.
Put layer of potatoes, onions and cheese until they are all used up.
Season with pepper and parsley.
Pour milk over the top.
Bake at 350° until hot. This can also be heated in a microwave.
Mix well before serving.

title: baked pineapple(goes great with ham)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in quart size baking dish. Add sugar; stir.
Add pineapple; stir.
Break bread into pieces and add to pineapple mixture.
Stir in melted butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix; put in covered dish.
Bake 5 hours in a 250° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Spray an 8 ounce Cool Whip container with vegetable spray. Put crab meat on bottom.
Mix cream cheese, onion and salts to taste.
Spread over crab meat and refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with cocktail sauce and serve with assorted crackers.
(Imitation crab meat works fine.)

title: english toffee
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 inch baking pan with 1 tablespoon butter; set aside.

In a heavy 3 quart saucepan, melt the remaining butter. Add sugar, corn syrup, and salt; cook and sir over medium heat until a candy thermometer reads 295 degrees (hard-crack stage). Quickly pour into prepared pan.
Let stand at room temperature until cool, about 1 hour.
In a microwave, melt chocolate chips; spread over toffee.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Let stand for 1 hour. Break into bite-size pieces.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature.
Yield:
about 2 pounds.

title: easy fresh apricot pie
directions: Prepare favorite pastry for 2 crust pie; line pie plate.
Fill with 3 cups fresh apricot halves.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; sprinkle over apricots. Drizzle 1 tablespoon lemon juice over fruit and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diane's squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Mix squash, onion, carrots, egg, mayonnaise and sugar.
Put 1/2 of cracker crumbs and cheese into buttered casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over crumbs, then add remaining cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned caramel icing
directions: In pan combine margarine, brown sugar, salt and milk.
Place on medium heat and stir until margarine is melted.
Boil gently for about 3 minutes.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cut up cauliflower and place in pan and cook for 10 minutes or until soft.
Scald light cream by bringing cream to a slight boil.
Melt butter in a big soup pot.
Stir in flour.
When well mixed, add chicken broth and cook until it begins to thicken slightly.
Add scalded cream, cauliflower, salt, white pepper and nutmeg.
Warm all together for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Dissolve the Jell-O in hot water and add to mix.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still hot, poke holes with a fork in the cake and pour the glaze over the top.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside; heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers. Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/3 of the meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, green bell pepper, red bell pepper and onion in a large bowl or container.
Mix together vinegar, water, celery seed, sugar, salt and mustard seed and bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add molasses and mix well.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Form balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Press down and bake at 350°.
Do not overbake if you want a soft, chewy cookie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery in butter.
Add broccoli; cook 5 minutes.
Mix together all ingredients, adding bread crumbs last.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Add grated cheese on top 5 minutes before done.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Mix ingredients, reserving small amount of grated cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers (Triscuits best choice).

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cook whole zucchini in boiling salted water for 8 minutes and drain.
Melt butter in skillet, add the Gruyere and cheddar and melt.
Add the sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Cut the zucchini in rounds and lay overlapping in a spiral circle in a round quiche dish.
Pour cheese mixture over the zucchini, sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 350 for 30 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter.
Add lemon rind and egg yolk.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into greased 9-inch cake pan (sides and bottom).
Mix apples with sugar and cinnamon. Fold in beaten egg white. Spread evenly over dough. Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add butter, egg and milk.
Beat hard 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cover with crunchy topping.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add chili mix following the directions on package.
Sprinkle garlic powder over top.
Pour in kidney beans with a cup of hot water.
Bring to a slow simmer and serve.
Can use ground turkey.

title: chocolate-coconut dessert(frozen)
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate in both kinds of milk.
Bring to boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, 4 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted. Chill.

title: millie's german coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Put 2/3 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; pour in pie filling and spoon in rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Beat on high speed until soft peaks form. Spread on cake and refrigerate.

title: special chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and soda in mixing bowl.
Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil in a saucepan.
Cool a little and add to first mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done in greased and floured, oblong cake pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and onions.
Cook until done.
Put in oleo and milk or cream.
Cook slow.
Stir.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: italian anisette rolls
directions: Add butter to scalded milk to soften. Make a well in flour and add salt, sugar, milk, butter, egg, flavoring and dissolved yeast. Mix to a soft dough. Let rise and double in size.
Break off three pieces the size of an egg and roll each piece into a rope.
Pinch rope together at one end and braid.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Let rise and bake at 425° until done.

title: "twinkie" filling for cupcakes
directions: Beat ingredients
together for 8 to 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Cut off tops of cupcakes and spoon out centers.
Fill with Twinkie filling and replace tops.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat sweet potato, vanilla, butter, sugar and egg until well mixed.
Bake
at
until
firm
minutes).
Mix topping of
brown
sugar,
chopped pecans, flour, coconut and melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake until brown at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, peanut butter and sugar; work together until smooth.
Press this mixture into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan. Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Spread over cracker mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: tomato salad
directions: Wash unpeeled tomatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in shallow dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste, along with sugar.
Do not mix.
In a bowl, mash together the onion, chives and marjoram.
Stir in olive oil.
When well mixed, pour a spoonful at a time over tomatoes.
Again, do not mix.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: slime
directions: Cook water and salt for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and quickly add cornstarch and rest of water; stir.
Return to heat to get desired texture.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serves 8.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown beef; drain and set aside. In same saucepan, saute onions, carrots, basil and parsley in 1 tablespoon margarine until tender. Add broth, potatoes and ground beef. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Mix milk with flour and add to soup with remaining ingredients. Simmer until cheese melts.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 tablespoons butter; stir until butter melts.
Cover and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking without stirring until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat. Without stirring, add remaining butter, pecans, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat mixture until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute green peppers and onions in butter.
Add soup and 1 1/2 cans water, taco seasoning and the vinegar.
Mix and simmer approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Place some of the chicken and a few spoonfuls of sauce in middle of tortillas.
Sprinkle some cheese on top of this and fold tortillas.
Place completed tortillas in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Pour remainder of sauce over rolled tortillas in pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, eggs, soda, salt, creamed corn, green pepper and pimientos.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a large iron skillet.
On top of this, layer the meat, onion, cheese and jalapenos.
Pour on other 1/2 of cornbread mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chris' scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in buttered medium hot skillet.
Scramble until done.
Pour eggs into serving dish and top with bacon bits.

title: marinated polish sausage
directions: Cover Polish sausage with water and bring to a boil.
Remove; rinse and set aside.
Put meat in bottom of slow cooker.
Place onion on meat.
Add sauce (remaining ingredients) on top.
Slow cook several hours, until onion is very tender.

title: garlic chip cookies
directions: Drop garlic cloves into boiling water for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Peel and chop garlic and soak in maple syrup for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, then stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drain garlic and add to cookie batter.
Blend well.
Drop batter by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick, easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with fruit.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Fruit will go to the bottom.
Serve with ice cream on the side.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sue's cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, 1 c. sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla until smooth. Pour into crumb crust and bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Beat sour cream, 1 tsp. vanilla and 1/2 c. sugar. Spread on top of cheese mixture and bake 7 minutes.

title: molasses sugar balls
directions: Combine ingredients; roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add berries together in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread with sour cream.
Mix remaining ingredients together to let set until they can be spooned on sour cream layer.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and refrigerate until firm.

title: broiled pork chops
directions: Mix enough A.1. sauce and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl to spoon over each pork chop.
You may use equal amounts of sauce. Sprinkle meat tenderizer on each chop.
Prick with fork.
Spoon mixed sauce on pork chops.
Place on broiler pan.
Spoon sauce on chops when turning them over.
Broil on each side until done.

title: easy pasta salad(make the day before.)
directions: Cook noodles; run cold water over. Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and tomato soup together and mix with noodles. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Season chicken with pepper and place in bowl with lemonade, stirring to coat.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Drain. Roll in cornflake crumbs, coating completely.
Place in melted butter in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: filbert cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, the margarine, shortening and egg.
Stir in flour, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls around filberts to form balls. Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until delicately brown, 12 to 15 minutes; cool.
Dip tops of cookies into Glaze, then into sugar.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 9-inch baking pan with butter (3 teaspoons).
In a mixing bowl, mix sugar and cocoa together and add 1/2 cup butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well. Add flour and salt; mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into pan. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into bars.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until set.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter until very soft.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, creaming after each addition until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Bake in four 9-inch layer pans, lined on bottom with paper, in a moderate 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn cheese casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, mustard and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks well.
Gradually stir in scalded milk and Tabasco sauce. Mix in cheese and corn.
Beat egg whites until stiff (not dry) and fold into mixture.
Pour into
a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Cover with cracker crumb mixture; spoon melted butter over top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until golden brown and slightly firm to touch.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning together.
Mix mashed avocado and sour cream together.

Mix onion and tomatoes together. On large platter, layer beans and taco seasoning mixture, then avocado and sour cream mixture, then some of both cheeses, then onion and tomatoes, then rest of cheeses, then green chilies and black olives on top.
Serve with nacho chips.
Better to make a day ahead and serve at room temperature.

title: fruit punch
directions: Stir to blend ingredients.
If desired, add one whole strawberry to each serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: marshmallow and peanut butter sandwich
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and peanut butter together; spread on bread.
If a bit stiff, add more peanut butter.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Disjoint and separate. Throw last tip.
Stir together ingredients.
Marinate in plastic bag.
Place this in bowl in refrigerator. Turn bag once or twice a day for 24 hours or more. When ready to bake, remove from marinade.
Place in pan lined with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown onion in skillet, then add meat in small pieces.
When meat is brown, add beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Pour prepared corn bread batter on top. Allow to bake until corn bread is done.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: rocky mountain apple bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, buttermilk, mayonnaise and vanilla until smooth.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and stir just until combined.
Core apples and chop.
Add to batter with raisins and nuts; stir just to mix.
Spread batter evenly in 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Test with a toothpick.)
Turn onto a rack to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: guacamole "dip"
directions: Slice avocados in half.
Scoop from skin.
Mash or whip avocado until creamy smooth.
Blend in sour cream and remaining ingredients.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook and cut chicken in bite size strips.
Heat soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for 5 minutes.
Heat oil and softened tortillas in oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Put chicken and 2 tablespoons soup mix in tortillas and roll up.
Place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch glass works well) and top with soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Stir in large bowl cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, milk and mushrooms.

title: chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: Arrange Banana slices on bottom of Crust; set aside.
Pour Milk into medium bowl.
Add Pie Filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into Crust. Cover with Whipped Topping.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: pineapple-carrot salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cold water, pineapple (with sugar) and salt. Refrigerate until slightly thickened, but not set.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into 4-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate until firm. Unmold on salad greens.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place in buttered baking dish. Top with seasoned bread crumbs. Strip with bacon to cover top. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in margarine.
Mix cornstarch and seasonings into pizza sauce and add sauce to meat/onion mixture. Stir well.
When mixture thickens and bubbles, add cheese (by thirds), stirring well after each addition.
Serve/heat in crock-pot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil vegetables until tender and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except for stuffing.
Layer stuffing on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add squash, then top with layer of stuffing.
Bake at 350° until warm.

title: peanut butter chip bars
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Place marshmallows on top. Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes until puffy.
Mix together syrup, butter, vanilla and peanut butter chips in pan until melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Put on top of marshmallows.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and simmer 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: meadow muffins
directions: Lightly grease muffin cups with a little bit of fat.
Add flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a bowl.
Put shortening in small skillet.
Heat until melted.
Remove skillet from heat. Let cool slightly.
Break egg into a small bowl.
Beat with egg beater until smooth.
Add milk.
Add shortening.
Make hollow in center of flour mixture.
Add milk mixture.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill cups half full.
Add teaspoon jelly to each.
Just cover with batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: nellie's butter squares
directions: Beat egg yolks and water until bowl is full.
Add sugar and beat until dissolved.
Measure cake flour after sifting once.
Add baking powder and salt to flour and sift three times.
Beat flour into first mixture.
Add vanilla to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares.
Frost top and sides with frosting.

title: holiday bread
directions: Mix in order and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about 40 or 50 minutes.

title: baked beans 1
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 2 to 2 1/2-quart baking dish and cook in the oven at 450° for 45 minutes to an hour or in the microwave for 30 minutes or until done the way you want your beans done.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Dust inside of pie crust with 1 or 2 tablespoons of flour. Fill shell to heaping with rhubarb pieces.
Beat together eggs and sugar, then pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy does it cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuit in butter, then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place prepared biscuit on edge in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and cook until clear. Add ground beef and brown.
Pour off fat.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water (1 cup).
Add tomato sauce and bouillon cubes (dissolved in water) to meat. Stir well until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring frequently, to prevent burning.
Texture should be thick.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients, except nuts.
Roll in ball and chill. Remove and roll in chopped nuts.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt over low heat; cook until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly for about 20 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
If it becomes too thick, add a little water.
Good over ice cream or pound cake.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread dough in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (ungreased).
Combine margarine and brown sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Pour evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate, brickle and milk chocolate.
Slightly swirl partly melted pieces.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes and make a thin syrup. Pour boiling syrup over crushed mint leaves and stems in deep mixing bowl. Cover mixture with tight lid and let it stand for about 1 hour. Add juice and grated rind and mint syrup in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together except for the taco chips and add them just before serving.

title: taco pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in olives, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in 8-inch pie pan or rectangular pan. Press rolls on bottom and sides of pan.
Sprinkle corn meal over rolls.
Spoon meat mixture over corn meal.
Spread sour cream on top of meat, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until the crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.
Serve with sliced lettuce, tomato and avocado.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Toss apples and cranberries with flour, sugar and cinnamon. Mound into 1 pie crust.
Dot with margarine and top with second crust.
Make several slits in top of crust near center.
Bake at 45 to 50 minutes at 450°.
Cool on wire rack.
Drizzle with confectioners icing, if desired.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Put just enough flour to make slightly stiff.
Pinch off in little balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Not very sweet.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, zucchini, salt, pepper and egg yolks.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into pancake mixture.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into about 1/4 inch of hot oil in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve immediately with syrup, sugar, jelly or another topping you enjoy.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat and bones in Crisco.
Place meat, bones, water and seasonings in soup kettle.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add barley.
Cook another hour.
Cool and skim off excess fat.
Remove soup bones.
Puree tomatoes.
Add carrots, celery, onions, tomatoes and beans.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Use tuna for bottom layer.
Blend soup, milk and seasonings. Put 1/2 of the noodles on top of tuna.
Add liquids.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix together the sour cream, instant pudding and milk until thick and creamy.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with fruit.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: katherine's blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt stick of margarine in baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over margarine and pour blue berries on top. Bake for 1 hour at 300 degrees.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in bowl. Pour over milk-Tabasco mixture.
Soak for about 1 hour covered. Chill.
After chilled, turn chicken in mixture, then flour.
Dip in cream; roll once more in flour.
Fry chicken in 3 to 4 batches in deep fryer until richly browned.
Drain on paper towels. Serves 6 to 8.

title: low-fat protein banana-berry shake
directions: Blend 2 cups strawberries, bananas, orange juice and ice cubes in a blender until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and enjoy a healthful breakfast.
As an added plus you have a fiber filled meal with Vitamins A and C.

title: caramel apples
directions: Cook all the ingredients and mix well.
Put apple on chop stick into the caramel.
Twist it and hold for a few seconds. Spoon all over caramel and dip into chopped pecans.

title: seafood pasta
directions: In a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the capellini to desired doneness; drain.
Toss with melted butter and place in a large bowl.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
In large mixing bowl, combine soups, sauce and hamburger (be sure to drain hamburger before adding to mixture).
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Spread layer of Tostitos on bottom; pour hamburger mixture over chips and spread.
Sprinkle cheese generously on top.
Bake until cheese starts to melt at 15 minutes (or totally melted at 30 minutes).

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix well and store in a clean old spice bottle.

title: clear french dressing
directions: Using a wire whisk mix sugar, salt and mustard together.
Add oil, a little at a time.
Continue to use whisk.
Add vinegar a small amount at a time.
Whisk constantly.
Use over tossed green salad.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package, drain. Arrange in greased 2 qt. baking dish. Saute onion in butter till clear. Combine eggs, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion, bread crumbs and water. Mix well. Pour over broccoli. Bake @ 350 until brown and firm.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Mix next 4 ingredients with hamburger.
Fill each (cooked) manicotti noodle with hamburger mixture.
Place in 13 x 9-inch rectangle pan.
Cover with sauce and oregano.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, sprinkled over sauce, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until bubbly.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl, stirring with a spoon (not a mixer), until dry ingredients are moist.
Bake in 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; cream with sugar. Add eggs and other ingredients. Mix well. Pour into unbaked crusts and bake 40 minutes at 325°. Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients.
Melt margarine and Cheez Whiz in microwave; pour over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Roll the turkey around the dressing; add gravy over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Place in a prepared pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Wash and grate unpeeled cucumbers using grater with 1/2-inch holes.
Add vinegar and garlic salt.
Stir.
Cover and allow to stand overnight in refrigerator.
The next day, press out liquid. Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise in bowl.
Combine with cucumber and serve with crackers.

title: grilled rosemary chicken
directions: Marinade:
Place all ingredients, except chicken, in food processor and blend until almost smooth.
Taste, then add more salt and pepper if necessary.
Save 1 cup of marinade.
Pour marinade over chicken quarters, turning pieces to make sure they are thoroughly coated.
Cover and refrigerate; should marinate for at least 6 hours (can remain overnight).
The longer the better.

title: popcorn cracker jacks
directions: Pop corn and set aside.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes the brown sugar, Karo and oleo.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn and stir well to coat.
Put on 2 foil lined cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 225° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes to break apart.
Cool well and store in tightly covered container.
Can add cooked peanuts to popcorn before pouring syrup over mix.

title: bean dip
directions: Top with grated cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana-pineapple nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or four 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes for large pans or about 40 minutes for smaller loaves.
A toothpick inserted into center of each should come out clean when loaves are done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Remove to wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Line 11 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs, mixed with 1/4 cup oleo.
Press in, forming crust, and refrigerate.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Blend and press in pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Melt margarine; mix with cake mix.
Will be crumbly.
Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mixture over cherries evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creamy bass fillets
directions: Place fillets in a single layer in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread the spinach over the fillets.
Heat margarine, cream, wine and lemon juice until almost boiling.
Pour over the spinach covered fillets. Cover with aluminum foil; bake in the oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: watermelon star salad
directions: Wash and pat dry 1 leaf of lettuce with a paper towel.
Place lettuce leaf on the salad plate.
Cut 1/2 slice of watermelon into 5 wedges 1 inch thick.
Trim red melon away from white part and green rind.
On lettuce leaf, arrange melon in a circle with the points outward to form a star.
Spoon 1/2 cup creamed cottage cheese into the center of the watermelon star.
Wash and sprinkle 1 tablespoon blueberries over the cottage cheese.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly and put in a 9 x 13 casserole. Melt butter, sugar, curry powder and dash of salt. Heat until sugar dissolves and pour over fruit. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jelly bean and beer pancakes
directions: Mix liquid into pancake mix to desired consistency.
Heat pan. Melt butter; mix into batter.
Add 1 or 2 handfuls of jelly beans. Cook and enjoy.

title: almond hershey pie
directions: Melt candy bars and marshmallows in double broiler.
Let cool and add cool whip.
Pour into pie crust.

title: italian macaroni and vegetables
directions: Cook macaroni and cut up skinned chicken into pieces.
Cut up vegetables (top of broccoli only).
In a large frying pan, cook chicken in olive oil.
Add the veggies and continue frying until veggies are done medium.
Add garlic and onion.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Add macaroni and stir.
Add oregano and cheese.
Cook approximately 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Soften margarine and cheese at room temperature.
Cream together until blended.
Add English peas and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with crushed crackers over top. Pour milk over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chunks and nuts with wooden spoon and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to rack and cool completely.
Makes approximately 36-48 cookies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first six ingredients thoroughly.
Do not heat.
Add onions and as many sliced cucumbers as can be contained in the liquid mixture (about 1 gallon jar).
Refrigerate 5 days before eating.
These will keep for 1 year in the refrigerator.

title: i love one pot meal
directions: You will need 1 Dutch oven pan or regular large pan.

title: crab-avocado dip
directions: Drain and slice crab.
In blender, combine avocado, lemon juice, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Blend until smooth. Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Fold in crab.
Cover and chill. Serve with crisp vegetables or chips.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions, using the seasoning packet; set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan; stir in flour until well blended.
Gradually stir in milk and broth; cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add sauce to cooked rice; mix in chicken, mushrooms, green pepper, pimiento and salt.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle top with toasted almonds and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender, season with salt while cooking. When chicken is done debone and set aside. Strain the chicken broth from the chicken and add to that broth the cans of chicken broth then add butter. Bring to a boil. Add pinches of the canned biscuits; until desired thickness. Remove from heat and add chicken. Blend well.

title: walnut mocha cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times.
Alternately add coffee and flour ingredients. Add walnuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Combine
butter, cocoa, water, buttermilk and eggs in a small saucepan.
Let bubble over low heat, stirring constantly after
it bubbles.
Combine	sugar,	flour,	baking	soda and vanilla in
a bowl.
Mix well and combine with first mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pimiento pepper
directions: Combine together and cook for 1 hour.
Put into clean jars and seal.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, pork, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, 2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg and milk.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, egg and sugar well.
Add bananas (mash them first) and flour and mix well.
Add soda.
Add nuts last if you are using them.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(To make a large loaf, double the recipe.)

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken; dip in milk; then corn flakes.
Bake in Teflon pan at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: seafarer's dinner
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a 1 1/2-quart covered round casserole dish, layer potatoes, carrots, onion and perch.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon dill and salt and pepper.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Repeat with remaining potatoes, carrots, onion, perch, dill weed, salt, pepper and margarine.
Cover.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Continue baking, uncovered, for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix ingredients to get good modeling consistency.
Let kids create sculptures and then gobble them up at clean up time.

title: apple salad
directions: Beat the egg with the flour and the whipping cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it boils and thickens.
Take off burner and add the sugar and vanilla.
Pour onto the apples and walnuts and mix.

title: hot mulled wine
directions: In a 5-quart kettle, combine sugar, cloves, cinnamon sticks and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, uncovered, 5 minutes and remove from heat, adding sliced lemons. Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes. With a slotted spoon, lift out the cloves and cinnamon sticks. Add brandy and wine.
Simmer until hot.
Serve in mugs. Can be stored, covered, in refrigerator. Makes 25 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Sift and mix well the dry ingredients; set aside. Measure milk. Separate eggs; put yolks in milk and whites in separate bowl to beat stiff.

(Any yolk in the egg whites will keep them from forming stiff peaks.) After beating the egg whites, use the mixer to mix the milk and eggs, then put into flour mixture and mix well. Then add the oil and mix.
Fold the egg whites into the mix. Do not overmix after adding egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron 2 minutes each.
Yields approximately 10.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on top of stove until thick, stirring until mixture is real thick.
If mixture gets lumpy while cooking, can use mixer to smooth.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together:
Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Blend in 2 eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats and semi-sweet chocolate pieces.

title: strawberries
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into balls. Chill one hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Chill.
Put green food color on almond slivers.
Roll strawberries in red sugar, then dip the end of the strawberry in green sugar.
Put almond slivers in one end of the strawberry for stem.
Makes 45.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears and salt to taste.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, eggs, soup and onion together well.
Spread some of mixture on bottom of casserole dish.
Place a layer of broccoli and continue until all of mixture and broccoli have been used. Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm herb dressing (dry).
Dot with butter and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave zucchini bake(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: In a 2-quart glass casserole, combine zucchini and butter. Cover and cook for 5 minutes on High power.
Combine eggs and cheese; stir into zucchini.
Cook, covered, on Simmer or Defrost for 10 minutes.
Rotate after 5 minutes.
Top with onion rings. Cook, uncovered, on Defrost for 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: brown rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole or bowl, combine onion, garlic and olive oil, microwave uncovered on High for 1 minute. Stir rice, water, orange juice, water chestnuts and tamari; microwave, uncovered on High 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and mushrooms; cover and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes; covered, before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza pasta casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in onions, olives, mushrooms, pepper, oregano, salt and pepperoni.
Cook noodles; drain. Combine with pizza sauce, milk, 8 ounces Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Stir meat mix into the noodles.
Sprinkle leftover cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple dabble cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Meanwhile in saucepan combine brown sugar, butter and milk; boil 4 minutes. Let cool a little.
Pour over cake.
Let cool at least 1 hour before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine raisins and walnuts with 1/2 cup flour in bowl; toss to coat well.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil in mixer bowl.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Add remaining 2 1/2 cups flour.
Add cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in raisin mixture.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until bread loaves test done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: beef rouladen(very old recipe from germany; a terrific treat.)
directions: VARIATION: Add water to beef broth; bacon salts it enough.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Melt and
brown
cup
sugar, in an iron skillet on medium-high heat, stirring often, until it gets black looking, with lid on skillet.
Slightly lift lid and add boiling water. Stir and take off stove and let cool.

title: garnet punch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in a punch bowl.
Float scoops of sherbet in punch.
Serve immediately.
Yields 22 (1/2 cup servings).

title: seasoned black-eyed peas
directions: Cover peas with water and bring to a boil.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Combine peas, water, bouillon, onion, pepper, garlic, thyme, vegetable oil and salt in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; cover and simmer gently for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 6 c. bundt pan. Beat margarine in large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy. Beat in brown sugar, yogurt, whole egg, egg whites and 3 Tbsp. lemon juice. Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl. Add flour mixture to margarine mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix in 2 Tbsp. poppy seeds and lemon peel. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake about 40 minutes or until cake is golden brown and wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan to wire rack; cool completely. For lemon glaze, mix powdered sugar with 2 Tbsp. plus 1 1/2 tsp. lemon juice until of desired consistency. Spoon glaze over cake and sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. poppy seeds.

title: alabama pound cake
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Bake at 325° on top rack of oven about 1 hour, until top is golden brown.

title: polish cake
directions: Beat ingredients and put in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until done.
The cake will be dark brown.
Test with toothpick.

title: mexican luncheon
directions: Brown sausage, onions and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Wash and stem tomatoes.
Dry completely.
Cook bacon until very crisp; drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, olive oil, salad and basil.
Pour over tomatoes; crumble bacon over all and stir to coat tomatoes with dressing.
Serve at once or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients (except the cheese).
Layer half the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spread with half the Ricotta mixture, then half the meat sauce and then half the Mozzarella.
Repeat, using the rest of the noodles, mixtures and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in skillet; season.
Add whole tomatoes, sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Put in pan, in layers, beginning with noodles, then meat, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: orange chicken
directions: Coat chicken with onion flakes, paprika and rosemary.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour orange juice over the chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel skins off potatoes.
Cut potatoes in thin slices, but not all the way.
Put potatoes in baking dish and cool them lightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rudolph sandwich
directions: Cut bread into triangles.
Spread with peanut butter.
Use raisins for eyes, pretzel sticks for antlers and 1/2 maraschino cherry for nose.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and use with vegetables for dipping.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and yeast.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and knead until smooth.
Cut biscuits into 2-inch circles.
Dip in butter and place onto pan; fold in half. Refrigerate until needed.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fancy franks
directions: Cut wieners in half.
Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around each 1/2 of wiener; secure with toothpick.
Put in crock-pot.
Pour brown sugar over.
Cook about 2 hours or until all syrup is absorbed into franks.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar,
vanilla,
whipping cream and half and half. Pour into
ice
cream freezer.
Add regular milk to fill line. Stir well.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots. Pour mixture over carrots. Put in tight container. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: french potato salad
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes, covered, in boiling salted water for 20 to 25 minutes, or until just tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Combine oil, vinegar, consomme, green onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss gently with sliced potatoes.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
If desired, serve on individual lettuce lined plates.

title: golden oyster stew
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Add mushrooms; cook 1 minute over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually.
Stir until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add oysters, potato soup, pimento and liquid hot pepper sauce.
Heat 5 or 10 minutes until oysters begin to curl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to cream cheese, mixing well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening. Stir in orange juice and egg.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Put in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool for 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Can be stored in the freezer.

title: molded easter eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients for stiff dough.
Do not add water.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into shells.
Dot with butter (butter may be added to ingredients, melted).
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour or until firm.

title: stuffed cabbage roll
directions: In skillet add hamburger meat, onions, bell pepper, parsley, chili powder, red pepper and bouillon cubes.
Add cooked rice when all is done.
Roll in wilted cabbage sections, basted with tomato paste.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: bacon cheddar cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers or olive bread.

title: mandarin orange cake and icing
directions: For the cake, mix eggs into cake mix; fold in oranges and juice.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.
The cake should be kept in the refrigerator.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together for a great punch.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook in 350 oven for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and 1/3 cup powdered sugar in medium size bowl.
Cut in margarine until it resembles small peas.
Mixture will be dry and crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray.
Mix sugars, oleo and vanilla.
Beat in egg; stir in flour.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until brown, about 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sharon bivins' sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Shape dough into balls. (Dough is very soft.)
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° until cookies just barely begin to darken.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Mix Coke or Pepsi, catsup, mustard, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Tastes great.

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: Mix thoroughly all the ingredients and pour into lightly greased pan with lid.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
This freezes well.
Very good.
Serves 8.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&M's and peanuts.
Melt margarine, 1/2 cup oil and marshmallows.
Pour over popcorn mixture.

title: old virginia sweet potato pudding
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until well blended. Stir in milk and corn syrup.
In a small bowl, mix togehter the sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to the egg mixture and stir until well blended.
Add butter and stir in.
Peel and finely shred sweet potatoes, measure 4 cups.
Add to egg mixture and stir until well mixed.
Turn into the prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
Top should be golden brown.
Cool slightly and serve as is, or with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crunchy salad
directions: The amount of vegetables used will be determined by the number of people being served.
