Marinate the cauliflower, broccoli, beans and mushrooms in Italian dressing.
When ready to serve, add the tomato slices and cheese.

title: frances' egg thing
directions: Beat milk, eggs, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper. Sprinkle croutons on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over croutons. Pour egg mixture over all. Can crumble 4 slices bacon on top. Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, peppers, onions, salt and 1/2 of the nuts.
Form into a log or ball and roll in other half of the nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 25 to 30 guests.

title: hot lemonade
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into mugs.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: wine
directions: Put sugar in a 5-gallon glass container (I use about 7 pounds of sugar).
Add just enough water to dissolve the sugar.
Add bottled pure grape juice and can of frozen grape juice.
Add enough water to bring the level to about 4 1/2 gallons.
Crumble yeast cakes and add to mixture.
Cover opening of bottle with 2 layers of Saran Wrap and secure it with rubber bands.
Let it stand in a dark closet until all bubbling stops or about 30 days. Siphon into bottles.
Happy drinking. . .

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan or electric frying pan and simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve warm with toothpicks.
Can be made one or two days ahead and reheated.

title: coconut icing
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients fairly rapid until firm ball forms in cold water.
Put egg whites in large bowl to beat.
Don't turn on stove until eggs are ready to beat.
Start cooking the first 3 ingredients and beat egg whites at same time.
When firm ball forms in cold water, pour over egg whites.
Add powdered sugar; beat real good.
Add salt, vanilla flavoring, or vanilla and coconut flavoring.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms leaving hollow mushrooms. Completely cook bacon, crumble into medium-sized bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom of 15
inch or 13
by
9 inch Pyrex pan.
Mix cheese, bacon and mayo in bowl.
Fill center of mushrooms heaping, but not over the sides.
Bake for 15 - 20 min., let cool for 2-3 min.
Enjoy!!

title: corn bread or muffins
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with corn meal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg slightly; add milk and shortening.
Combine with dry ingredients, stirring only until moist.
Pour into well-greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake in moderately hot 425° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: melba's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onion until tender.
Drain and pour in 2 1/2 quart casserole, then add all other ingredients.
Stir slightly. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Compliments every time!

title: bayou baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon; remove and drain.
Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Pour beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir bacon and onions into beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rouge camion feu(red velvet cake)
directions: Mix soda and vinegar.
Set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring in a cup and add to sugar, eggs and shortening mixture.
Add buttermilk with salt, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in vinegar and soda mixture carefully but well.
Bake in two nine inch pans at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Split cooled layers and ice between layers and on top. Decorate with colored coconut, nuts, etc. as desired.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package in a large size skillet or pan.
Brown ground beef and saute onion and pepper (green).
Drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese), including corn and bean liquids.
Mix well and pour into casserole or baking dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake and remove bones and skin from salmon.
Blend in eggs and salmon-milk mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add some flour, then beaten egg yolks and rest of flour.
Dough is very thick.
Spread it into ungreased pan and pat dough up the sides.
Bake dough at 300° for 17 to 20 minutes, then spread filling on hot dough.

title: bubble-up pizza
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters in a large bowl. Add sauce and stir. Add 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam). Add additional toppings on top and then top with remaining cheese. Cheddar cheese may also be added.

title: italian chocolate spice cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, spices and cocoa together.
Add milk, jam and orange extract.
Mix flour and baking powder together, then add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts, raisins and chocolate chips.
Roll cookies into small balls (1-inch).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with a thin frosting mixture of confectioners sugar and milk.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches, place 2 teaspoons butter, brown sugar and 3 nut halves.
Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Heat until melted.
Combine and mix applesauce and milk until dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Spoon into cups.
Bake 10 minutes in oven at 450°.
Turn over to release from pan.

title: coconut wheaties
directions: Dissolve the brown sugar in the Wesson oil, then add vanilla, eggs and sugar.
In another bowl, add the remaining ingredients. Add ingredients of the first bowl to the second bowl; mix well with a spoon or fork.
Roll into large, marble size balls and place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 357° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Fry
bacon and then retain half of the drippings in the skillet.
Saute onions in bacon grease and add crumbled bacon, vinegar,
water
and
brown
sugar.
Wash all beans except the baked
beans.
Add all beans and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream
the
butter
and
sugar.
Add
vanilla.	Beat in eggs. Add
flour,
cocoa and salt.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of flour over
nuts and fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
When cool, frost.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables. Heat oil in large frypan or wok.
Add beef and cook over high heat until browned.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat until tender.
Turn up heat and add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.

title: pineapple mandarin chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Spread crushed pineapple and orange sections evenly over chicken.
In a small bowl, combine orange juice and cornstarch, stirring to dissolve cornstarch.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add enough milk for spreading consistency.
Very good with chips or crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put into prepared chocolate cookie pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Peel eggplant, dice.
Cook with onion in small amount of boiling salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) until very tender.
Drain.
Cool.
Add egg and mix well, mashing eggplant. Add salt, pepper and cracker crumbs, mix.
Pat rounded tablespoons of mixture into patties on board sprinkled heavily with corn meal; turn patties and press thin.
Pan-fry quickly in generous amount of hot oil until brown and crisp.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper 5 minutes.
Add flour and milk. Stir and cook until thickened; season.
Add ham and potatoes. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie shells with pecans.
Beat remaining ingredients together until well blended.
Pour over pecans, dividing evenly between shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is firm.

title: mother's apple relish
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling point.
Add chopped peppers, onions and apples.
Cook until done.
Can and seal.

title: don's favorite scottish mince
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet or heavy pot and drain fat.
Add broth or water to cover.
Add onion and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, adding water if needed.
When cooked, add a handful of oatmeal to thicken mixture slightly.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice well.
Add 1 quart sliced strawberries.
Pour into crusts and chill.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Put cherry pie filling in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Add cherry jello (use only 1 cup water).
Mix pineapple with lemon jello (use pineapple juice and water to make 1 cup).
When partially set, layer on top of cherry jello.
Spread Cool Whip to top and sprinkle with toasted pecans.

title: self-stick plastic(a sheet of plastic from a puddle of glue)
directions: Will need 8-inch square plastic wrap, tape, tray or cookie sheet, small dish, spoon and scissors.

title: dried peas with rice and tomatoes
directions: Soak the peas overnight.
Cook until tender.
Add the well washed rice, onions, tomatoes and seasoning.
Cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter and set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Place in baking dish and top with pecans.
Chill until served, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add 7-Up and chill until partially set.
Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until firm. Combine sugar, flour, reserved juice and egg in heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and stir.
Cool; do not chill.
Add cream cheese; mix thoroughly. Fold in cream; spread evenly over jello mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: mushroom rolls
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, mushrooms, seasoned salt and a small amount of mushroom juice.
Separate rolls into three rectangles.
Spread cheese mixture on the rectangles and roll so they are long.
Slice each roll into 5 pieces.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients
and
refrigerate.
May be made a day before serving.

title: meat loaf and tater bake
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, eggs, onions, salt, pepper, ketchup and seasoned salt.
Pat in 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven, drain off excess fat. Combine 3 cups mashed potatoes and cheese; spread over meatloaf and bake for 1/2 hour more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Mix broth and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Slowly pour in egg.
Stir once gently.
Garnish with green onion.

title: oatmeal chocolate chippers
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk. Sift next 5 ingredients.
Mix into creamed ingredients well.
Stir in oats, chips and raisins.
Drop from a tablespoon 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool slightly on pan before removing.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saut onion in butter.
Boil squash in water; drain.
Add onion, soup, cracker crumbs and cheese to cooked squash.
Mix. Transfer to casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into 8x8 inch pan. Chill well and serve cold.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into Pam spayed baking dish. Bake at 350° until well done.

title: ranch chicken casserole
directions: Tear tortillas in small pieces.
Arrange ingredients into layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: boxer gloves
directions: Thaw dough.
Let rise until double.
Cut loaf into 8 equal pieces.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Stretch and pull.
Deep fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: hot crab dip elegante
directions: Melt cream cheese in top pan of a double boiler set over low heat. Blend in mayonnaise, garlic, onion, mustard, sugar and salt. Stir in crab meat and wine.
Heat through.
Recipe can be doubled. Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: blueberry strata pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of baked crust.
In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Beat in whipped topping.
Place cream cheese mixture in pie crust; top with pie filling.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Put into a baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mint sherbet
directions: Bruise the mint leaves; add the lemon juice and let them stand, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dissolve sugar in water and boil without stirring until a fine thread spins.
Take from fire; add the mint and lemon juice.
Add orange juice.
Cool and strain.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry
ingredients together and add last three ingredients. Mix until
all
are
mixed up.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.	Pour into baked pie shells.

title: crispy macaroni and cheese
directions: Blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Stir in cooked macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings and remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in the shortening.
Beat in the milk and eggs.
Stir into dry ingredients the blueberries.
Grease a 9-inch tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Before removing from pan, while still warm, drizzle with glaze.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream
together the sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs. Dredge all
fruit
in part of the flour, about 1/2 cup.
Sift together remaining
flour,
soda
and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add sweet
milk
and
juice
(juice from maraschino cherries is especially good).
However, additional milk may be substituted. Next,
add
dredged
fruit
and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon
on greased cookie sheet and bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: no name cookies
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar, peanut butter and oleo. Press into a large cookie sheet.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix well all
ingredients
in
mixer.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Cook in
oven
30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins. Four muffins equal 1
cereal or bread serving, 1 fruit serving and 1 milk.

title: reese's bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add powdered sugar, crumbs and peanut butter. Mix well and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill about another 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberry filling, pineapple and milk together.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry-peach upside-down cake
directions: Arrange peaches in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine strawberry and peach flavor jello and cinnamon in small bowl. Sprinkle about 3/4 of mixture evenly over peaches; dot with butter.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 3/4 of the batter over batter in pan.
Swirl spatula through batter to marble.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean and cake pulls away from side. Cool in pan on wire rack for about 5 minutes.

title: french market soup
directions: Wash beans; place in bowl.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Next day, drain off water.
Add 3 quart of fresh water, ham hock and bay leaves.
Simmer, covered for 3 hours.
Add other ingredients except sausage and chicken.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add chicken and sausage; simmer until chicken is done. Remove bones.
Serve piping hot.

title: fruit delight cake
directions: Preheat oven to cake box setting.
Mix up regular cake mix. In cake pan, melt butter and pour in blueberry pie filling; spread and then pour cake mixture over filling.
Bake at regular cake setting.
Mix package of cream cheese into a bowl along with can of icing.
Mix well.
Drain pineapple.
When cake is cool, spread on icing and top with pineapple chunks.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients until blended.
Add sauerkraut, pimentos and onion; toss well.
Cover and refrigerate one to three days before serving.
Keeps a long time.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Scrub clams and soak them in three changes of cold water to remove the sand.
Steam the clams over one cup water for 8 minutes until the shells open.
Discard the shells and chop clams into small pieces.
Strain the broth through cheesecloth to remove any sand.
Boil the potatoes in salted water for 15 minutes.
Fry bacon in a saucepan until one tablespoon of fat has rendered. Remove the bacon.
Fry the onion for 3 minutes in bacon fat.
Add strained clam broth or broth from canned clams.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt oleo and chips, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Add rest of ingredients until just combined. Spread mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will be soft but will firm up when cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: aunt dot's cracker fudge
directions: Line a jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with 1-inch sides) with foil. Grease well. Line the pan with Club crackers and set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir.
Add bananas.
Fold in flour and chopped nuts.
Pour in well-greased pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla in large bowl; lay a stick of margarine on top and cook in microwave on Medium-high, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until margarine is melted, then take out.
Stir and mix nuts, if desired.
Pour in a greased pan or pie plate.
Chill until firm for about 1 hour in freezer; cut in squares and eat!

title: quick and easy kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ginger ale, and put in refrigerator in a gallon jar until ready to serve.
Add 1 quart ginger ale just before serving.
Thinly sliced oranges can be used to float on top and make it pretty.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat with mixer.
Combine sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs.
Slowly add flour and milk alternately; add flavoring.
Grease large Bundt pan (use sugar instead of flour to coat pan).
Place in cold oven; set at 325°.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon cheese cake pie
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Add the sugar and whole egg. Mix well.
Add flour, then milk.
Stir in lemon juice and peel. Pour into unbaked cracker pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Chill and serve.
(May be topped with sour cream.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 3 cake pans (each 8-inches in diameter).
Mix together all ingredients, using electric mixer.
Divide batter among prepared cake pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until layers test done. When completely cool, frost cake with Pineapple Icing. Refrigerate.

title: marinade for wild game
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl just large enough to cover game with water.
Soak frozen or fresh game overnight in the refrigerator.
No need to stir marinade.
Use for red meat or game birds.

title: cherry salad
directions: Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: earl stones sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Peel, slice crosswise and boil potatoes until tender. Put them in a deep pie plate lined with pastry dough. Put a sauce over potatoes made of remaining ingredients. Cover with dough and bake in slow oven.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash and slice (do not peel) tart apples.
Place bacon drippings in skillet and heat to 400°.
Add apples and cook, covered, for 8 minutes.
Dust lightly with flour and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar to taste and cook until apples are light brown.

title: chicken diane(serves 4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of each, butter and oil, in large skillet.
Cook chicken 4 minutes on each side over high heat.
Transfer to warm dish.
Add chives, parsley, brandy, lemon juice and mustard to pan.
Whisk constantly for 15 seconds.
Add broth until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in butter and oil and pour over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: punch
directions: Put in gallon jug and finish filling with water.
Add Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise.
Take out yolks and mash with fork until no more lumps.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, mustard, mayonnaise.
Mix well.
With teaspoon, heap the yolk mixture into hollow whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix all above ingredients and place in a 13x9-inch pan.

title: apricot balls
directions: Combine apricots and coconut.
Add milk and mix well.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook all macaroni together; drain.
Heat pepperoni in pan until there is enough oil to saute onions and green peppers.
Add macaroni.
Use small amount of spaghetti sauce just to well coat the ingredients.
Place in long casserole dish.
Best if not too deep and top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: lemon-glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in saucepot; cover with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, melt margarine. Add brown sugar, lemon juice and salt; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Drain carrots; add margarine mixture and toss gently. Yield: 6 servings.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain liquid off dill spears and rinse.
Slice pickles.
Mix all the other ingredients together; mix well and put into jar. Add sliced pickles and store in the refrigerator.
Shake often.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Blend ingredients by hand.
Add a little of reserved pineapple liquid, if it seems too dry.
Spread between layers of cakes and on top and sides.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jerry norton peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy pan bring 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Add sugar and syrup.
Cook till it spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook till golden brown, until you think its going to burn.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grind beef, veal and pork together 3 times.
Soak crumbs in warmed cream.
Combine crumbs and meat.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk. Add egg yolks, onion and seasonings.
Form meat into medium or tiny balls and brown on all sides in hot fat.
Add flour to 4 tablespoons of fat from pan and stir until it thickens.
Add beef broth and one cup water.
Heat until slightly thickened.
Strain. Add to meatballs.
Serve with noodles.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk, salts and Parmesan cheese until well mixed.
Layer broccoli, chicken and sauce.
Layer again.
Top with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: idelle's beef stew
directions: Brown meat slowly in fat on all sides in large pan.
Place sliced onions on top.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and pour over meat and onions.
Add spices and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
When tender, discard bay leaf and garlic.
Add vegetables and sliced chestnuts.
Sliced carrots, potatoes and onions may be cooked while meat mixture is simmering to eliminate additional cooking time and added at this point.
If using canned vegetables, add and heat thoroughly until tender.
Thicken gravy with 1/4 cup of flour blended with 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir into stew; stir until evenly blended.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: quick dinner idea
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir in ground beef in a 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, bell pepper, 2 Tbsp. flour, 1/2 tsp salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Pour into an ungreased rectangular pan 13x9x2-inch.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, 1 cup flour and 1/2 tsp. salt with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with onion.
Bake 25-30 minutes. or until puffy and golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in bottom of greased 9 x 12 pan. Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Next combine mayonnaise and chicken soup together and pour over chicken. Top with cheese and cover with bread crumbs.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Drain pineapple thoroughly.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix pineapple with grated cheese and flour mixture.
Place in casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour 1/2 cup melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: soap balls
directions: Whipped soap can be made with either soap or detergent.
Soap retains color in foam better and is easier to clean up, too.
Soap flakes give a better texture than powdered soap.
The child makes whipped soap himself.
First, s/he pours water into mixing bowl and adds soap flakes.
S/he beats soapy water with eggbeater until mixture is frothy, but not stiff.
(If soap gets too stiff, it will be too difficult to use because it gets too slippery to apply. Also it will crack when it dries.)
S/he stirs in color (food color or tempera).
Colors will be pale.
You can use without color to look like snow.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Coat chops with salt and pepper; brown.
Set aside.
Put sliced potato in casserole with onions, salt and pepper.
Stir soup well.
Pour over potato.
Lay chops on top and bake 1 hour at 350°
or until all is cooked through.

title: foccacia bread
directions: Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Flatten slightly and spray with olive oil spray.
Sprinkle with rosemary and onion and knead well to mix thoroughly.
Roll out dough to a 9 x 6-inch rectangle.
Place on 12 x 9-inch baking sheet.
Press out dough until it fills pan.
Spray bread with olive oil spray.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove and top with sauce, then layer zucchini, mushrooms and peppers.
Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake again for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: punch
directions: In a 4-quart container, combine apricot nectar, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour in lemon-lime beverage.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serve immediately.

title: ole timey chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, mix water, cocoa and shortening together and heat until shortening melts.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake pan at 350° until done.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Arrange in following layers in casserole dish:
peas, asparagus, mushroom soup and water chestnuts.
Top with grated cheese.
Cube bread and soak in melted margarine.
Lay bread cubes on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad dessert
directions: Bake pretzels on cookie sheet with 2 sticks butter at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer pretzels, then Cool Whip.
Spread cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Chill.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice from can.
Mix strawberries and pineapple with jello.
Pour atop cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: caramel custard
directions: Boil sweetened condensed milk for 1 1/2 hours in an unopened can.
Cook sugar and water over high heat until light brown.
Pour into a straight sided dish and coat bottom and sides.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar.
Blend.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add cream and sweetened condensed milk.
Place dish in 1-inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let set awhile and invert on plate, draining liquid.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet over medium heat, cook sugar until caramelized, stirring occasionally to remove lumps.
Pour into 9-inch ovenproof bowl to coat sides and bottom.
In blender or medium bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in Eagle Brand, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour into caramelized dish; set in larger pan.
Fill pan with 1/2-inch of water.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Loosen sides of flan with knife; turn out of pan to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook sugar, raisins and hot water 5 minutes and cool.
Add dry ingredients alternately with raisin mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake.

title: patty ann's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients except baking soda, chocolate chips, and nuts.
Soften butter/margarine and combine with wet ingredients.
Mix hot water and baking soda together and combine with wet ingredients.
Mix dry and wet ingredients and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop cookies by tablespoons onto greased and floured cookie sheets and bake in 350 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crock-pot baked bean combo
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel and crumble.
To bacon drippings, add other ingredients except beans.
Put in crock-pot and cover.
Cot and heat setting #5 for 20 minutes.
Add all beans and crumbled bacon.
Stir.
Cover and reduce heat to #3 for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain beans.
Cook bacon and reserve drippings.
Mix drippings, sugar, vinegar and onion.
Combine with beans.
Place in casserole dish.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: funday sunday
directions: Mix and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Peel as many white potatoes as you need for a 3-quart pot. Wash them and put in enough water to cover potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste and put 1 stick of margarine and cook until tender.

title: wilted cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon and reserve drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add onion, sugar, vinegar and salt to drippings in skillet, stirring until blended.
Stir in cabbage.
Cook over medium heat, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with reserved bacon.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add next 5 ingredients. Pour in baking pan and toast in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
When cool, store in tin boxes or cans.

title: rose's cookie bars
directions: Beat together first six ingredients until well mixed.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour into ungreased cookie sheet with edge.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut immediately and let cool in pan. Yummy!

title: best cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly, then add egg yolk and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Pat 1/3 of dough on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with sides removed.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 6 minutes or until golden; cool.
Butter sides of pan and attach to bottom.
Pat remaining dough evenly on sides to height of 2 inches.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: On low heat,
in iron skillet melt enough margarine to cover the surface of the pan.
Butter one side of each slice of bread, making sure to butter the opposite sides.
Place buttered side down on the skillet.
On one slice of bread, place rolled slices of corned beef (entire package) and place a generous amount of kraut evenly over the corned beef.
On the other slice of bread, cover entirely with Swiss cheese.
Heat until both sides are golden brown.
Then, cover kraut with Kraft's Thousand Island dressing.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell; bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake 45 minutes more or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and top with whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together, blending in sour cream and chocolate chips last.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, checking at 50 minutes.

title: caramel peanut bars
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and set 1 cup aside, put the rest in a 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt caramel and cream, stir often.	Sprinkle chocolate chips and peanuts over 9 X 13 mixture, put caramel mixture over top.
Sprinkle 1 c. reserve over top.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit frappe
directions: Boil water and sugar and allow to cool.
Mix all ingredients (except 7-Up) together and freeze in bowl.
When ready to use, take from freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Place in punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up over frozen mixture.

title: squash pie(tastes like coconut pie)
directions: Blend and pour into a
pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Boil chicken and take off bone.
Brown onion in butter (optional).
Mix all ingredients together and simmer.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add Crisco.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Cream thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Add milk, flour, baking powder, vanilla and lemon. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put in middle of cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Stir until all is mixed well.
Spread in buttered pan.
Put in freezer until frozen.
Cut in squares.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly (low heat).
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Place potatoes in greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish and pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: french onion rice
directions: Mix
soups,
rice
and water in a shallow pan.	Chip up the margarine on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave (uncovered) for 25 minutes on High.

title: lentil salad
directions: Soak and cook lentils according to package directions.
Drain and add other ingredients while still warm.
Stir.
Let sit for twenty minutes, so the tomatoes have time to soften and absorb some of the liquid before serving.
This keeps well.
I bring this to potluck dinners because it is safe unrefrigerated for hours and there are always people who appreciate a low-fat selection.

title: amy's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rod-iron skillet with 1/4 cup vegetable oil in oven to be heating while mixing other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in heated rod-iron skillet. Bake until top is golden brown.

title: pan bagna("moist bread")
directions: Cut French bread lengthwise; scoop out center, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Using food processor, process bread crumbs to finely chop; set aside.
Whisk together lemon juice, oil and garlic.
Stir in bread crumbs, tomato, pepper, scallions, olives, capers and thyme.
Mix well; season with salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into bread shell.
Serves 4.
Contains 115 cal, 2.5 gms fat, 4 gms pro, 19 gm cho, 0 chol, 10% cal from fat.

title: tex mex lasagna
directions: Last 3 ingredients, mix together and pour on.

title: ellen's fruit salad
directions: Cook puddings together with 3 cups liquid.
Use the liquids from the canned fruit and orange juice or Tang to make remainder of 3 cups.
Cool slightly, then add fruits.
Refrigerate.
May add maraschino cherries or grapes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburger meat in large iron frying pan until done and crumbles.
Pour off grease or fat.
Add soup to meat.
Mix well. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put ready mashed potatoes on top of soup and meat mixture evenly.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: football casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add onion, ketchup, steak sauce and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain. Combine macaroni and meat in casserole dish.
Season to taste. Blend in soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Contains 32 calories each.

title: *mamaliga
directions: Bring the water to a boil. Slowly add the cornmeal, stirring vigorously with wooden spoon until thick and smooth. Water should continue to boil.
Cover and leave on low heat about 10 to 12 minutes until meal takes the shape of the pan.
Run a knife around the edges and invert on a plate.
Serve hot, plain with melted butter, sour cream, grated cheese or fried eggs on top, etc.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Mix together chicken soup, onions, pimento and chili powder. Add chicken.
Place tortillas on bottom of casserole.
Pour mixture over them, then another layer of tortillas.
Repeat.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cornbread mix last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: nanny's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, vanilla and yolk.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Roll teaspoonful into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with heel of hand.
Brush with whipped egg white.
Bake for 5 minutes at 375°.
Keep a close eye on these, do not let cookies get too brown!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until softened.
Beat in sugar.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut and whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: key lime chiffon pie
directions: Blend first four ingredients and pour into pie crust. "Refrigerate."
That's it.
Serves 8.

title: fruit 'n' nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the apples, oranges, raisins, cherries and pecans.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well. Add to fruit mixture and stir to coat.
Chill.
Just before serving stir in bananas.

title: winter warm up open house punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon; add ginger ale.
Serve at once with cinnamon stirrers.
Makes about 2 quarts or 16 servings.

title: egg stada(good for breakfast for a group of 8 to 10)
directions: Secure one large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut into small cubes.
(This will take about 2 months.)
Put in large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover.

title: corn fritters(a good way to use up leftover creamed corn.)
directions: Drop by tablespoons into hot shortening.
(Leftover mashed potatoes can be used the same.)

title: beef jerky
directions: Prepare steak by trimming away fat.
Partially freeze to allow you to slice very thin, with the grain.
Combine other ingredients and marinate steak up to 48 hours.
Preheat oven to 125° and lay each strip across oven racks.
Leave oven open slightly to release moisture.
This is a drying process, not baking.
Dry at 125° for 12 hours or until chewy.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: fruit pops
directions: You will also need a large bowl, spoon, soup or punch ladle, measuring cups, ice cube tray or paper cups, wooden sticks or ice cream spoons.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and melted margarine.
Pat in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese (room temperature), confectioners sugar and eggs (beaten) and pour over the top of cake mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: In bowl, mix well first 7 ingredients.
Stuff about 3 tablespoons cheese mixture into each shell.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spread 1/2 of the spaghetti sauce.
Arrange shells, stuffed side up, in sauce.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain first 3 fruits.
Mix fruits together in a casserole, preferably a shallow one.
Add brown sugar.
Pour wine over fruit and dot with small amount of butter.
Cook in oven for 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.
When done, remove from oven and dot with sour cream just before serving.
This is a nice accompaniment to a main dish. Serves 6 to 8.

title: night-before french toast
directions: The night before serving, melt butter and brown sugar in a small pan, stirring.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay bread slices on top of brown sugar mixture.
Combine eggs with milk and cinnamon.
Pour over the bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: 15 minute chicken and rice
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken in hot oil covered for
8 minutes or until browned.
Set aside and pour off fat.
Add soup, water, paprika, and pepper.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Place chicken on mixture.
Cover and cook on low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir.
Serves 4. For creamier rice, increase water to 1 2/3 cups.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Stir eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients; add nuts.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350° in a greased pan. Cookies should be soft when taken from oven.
Cut in squares and leave in pan to cool.

title: maryann's cut-out cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, margarine and sour cream.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda and mix well.
Make soft dough and chill.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Drain in colander.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat tomatoes with this mixture.
Fry in cooking oil (heated) slowly until brown, turning once.

title: date chews
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Stir in dates, walnuts, eggs and almond extract.
Spread in a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: "candy nuts"
directions: Combine both kinds of sugar and sour cream and cook over medium heat, stirring.
Cook until a soft ball forms in a small amount of cold water (approximately 10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated (let cool a little).
Turn onto waxed paper.
With fork, separate the nuts.
Let dry.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream and pour in oblong cake pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over cake mix; swirl through.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Take cake out of oven and while hot, make small holes in cake.

title: nanny's famous buttermilk biscuits
directions: Using a fork, cut the shortening into the flour until crumbly. Use enough buttermilk (about 1/2 cup to start) to form dough. Keep adding buttermilk until the dough is a little wet.
Take floured hands; make medium size ball with dough.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with a little buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until lightly browned on top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover with corn flake crumbs and a little butter, bake for 30 more minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat butter, eggs and sugar.
Add salt, nutmeg, ginger and cinnamon.
Add pumpkin and milk.
Bake in raw pie crust at 400° for 15 minutes, then decrease oven to 350° and bake until set. (Wet knife inserted should come out clean.)

title: four layer strawberry cheesecake
directions: Place in 9 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until lightly browned).

title: fluffy frozen p-nut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese, beat in sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk and blend thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in shells. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Makes 3 pies.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat bacon oil.
Mix flour and tomato sauce and stir into oil. Add whole tomatoes and mash into gravy while cooking.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir often.
Cook until smooth and thick.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Add margarine and salt to water.
Bring to a boil.
Add grits slowly while stirring.
Turn down burner and add cheese while grits thicken.
Add eggs and Tabasco.
Stir well.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley/pecans.
Chill mixture.
Shape in balls; roll in chopped pecans or parsley. Makes up to 3 balls.
Can freeze.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute beef, onion and peppers. Drain well and set aside.
Mix together corn meal, salt and soda. Add eggs, oil, milk and corn. Grease a large iron skillet (cold).
Pour 1/2 of the batter in skillet. Add meat mixture and top with cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top. (Start in cold oven.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake corn bread as directed on package.
Crumble in large bowl.
Saute onions and bell peppers until soft.
Add to corn bread.
Add cream-style corn, pimentos (drained), dry soup and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add chicken broth to desired moistness. Pour into 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.

title: italian pasta and veggie salad
directions: Blanch broccoli in boiling water for 1 to 2 minutes and drain. In mixing bowl, combine Ranch dressing, Parmesan cheese and black pepper.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pasta and all vegetables. Mix well. Add dressing to pasta and mix thoroughly.

title: rhubarb pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add vanilla to milk, then add alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Spread with rhubarb, nuts and pineapple.
Cover with batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before inverting on large platter.
Serve with scoops of ice cream or gobs of whipping cream.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar; bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1 large box jello.
Stir until dissolved. Pour in jars and cook.
Put in deep freeze.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well. Microwave on High for 14 to 15 minutes.
Stir in baking soda. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture starts to thicken, approximately 3 minutes.
Working quickly, drop by tablespoon onto either a greased cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip holiday cookies
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and salt in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg yolk.
Gradually beat in flour; stir in 1 1/2 cups of morsels.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll half of dough to 1/4 inch thickness between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Remove top sheet of wax paper. Cut into shapes; chill for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Spread with frosting or decorate however.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar and nutmeg.
Combine well-beaten egg, milk and 5 Tbsp. melted butter; add to sifted ingredients and blend lightly (about 25 strokes). Cover the bottom of greased 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin pans with batter;
add 6 or 8 blueberries to each cup and cover with more batter to half fill the pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Remove muffins from pans and immediately dip the top into melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Makes 12 muffins.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in frypan.
You can finish frying the meatballs in frypan until completely cooked or you may finish them in the oven until cooked through.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs and rinse with very cold water.
Peel eggs and slice in half, reserving yolks in processor bowl.
With steel knife process yolks until fluffy with no lumps.
Add remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture and garnish with crumbled bacon or olives.

title: resurrection rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop ppocorn.
Remove unpopped corn.
Put popcorn in large bowl. Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook until forms hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn and mix together.
Butter hands and roll into balls.

title: tuna melts
directions: Preheat broiler. Combine first 6 ingredients. Spread 3 tablespoons tuna mixture onto each muffin half. Top each with 1 tomato slice and 1 tablespoon cheese. Broil 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge cake squares
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Melt margarine in water and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat well. Combine baking soda and buttermilk; add to batter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured (or sprayed) 10 X 15 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is still hot, frost with marshmallow fudge frosting.

title: amish peanut butter
directions: Blend all ingredients.
If not easy to spread, add a little warm water.

title: poke sallet
directions: Wash poke sallet real good.
Put in a large kettle.
Add hog jowl and salt and cook until sallet is tender.
If you like, fry the sallet in meat grease.
Serve with deviled eggs and cornbread.

title: date log
directions: Combine oleo, dates, sugar, egg and vanilla in large saucepan. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add cereal and pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into two 11-inch logs and roll in coconut.
Cool and slice thin.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix egg with corn and milk, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in hot (450°) oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook for 20 to 25 minutes more.
Leftover ham or tuna fish may be added for a tasty main dish.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Defrost lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Add Eagle Brand slowly to mixture, stirring continuously.
(May add squirt of lemon juice to make tart.)
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate several hours.
Add Cool Whip to top or sliced fruit (kiwi fruit, strawberries, peaches).

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream in a bowl, mixing well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Completely crush, 1 layer at a time, ripe berries.
To 2 cups berries, add 4 cups sugar.
Mix well.

title: martha's ham
directions: You will also need 1 large cooking bag.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients, except the onion rings in a casserole in order given.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
During the last 5 minutes, add onion rings on top to brown and crisp. Serves 8.

title: dad's clam chowder
directions: In a kettle, fry bacon; remove bacon pieces and reserve.
Cook onions in fat until straw colored.
Add potatoes, boiling water, tomatoes, celery, carrots, green pepper, bay leaves, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add caraway seed, clams and clam liquid; simmer for another 5 minutes. Serve in a hot tureen.
Sprinkle top with bits of crisp bacon.

title: holiday peas
directions: In a saucepan, brown rice with sage and butter.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add peas; simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Stir in pimento.

title: simple fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit cocktail and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix together the rhubarb, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup sugar. Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan; dot with butter.
Mix together the remaining sugar, 1 cup flour, egg and baking powder.
Pour over rhubarb; bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: cheesy chicken corn soup
directions: Cream together the soup and broth. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce and simmer 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Serve with tortilla chips. Freezes well.

title: cherry delight
directions: Press in bottom of an 11 x 11-inch pan the cracker crumbs and melted margarine.

title: zenobia bryant's break away bread
directions: In large
bowl	combine boiling water and Crisco.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.	Roll
out
1/2-inch
thick.
Cut
with round glass and dip each piece in melted butter.
Lay in greased pan about half full and
let
rise
hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yields 2 loaves.

title: hearty spam soup
directions: Cook 10 minutes at boiling and then simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.
Cool.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions; drain. Combine with next 6 ingredients.

title: mom's chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Arrange peas and carrots over top.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl; add milk and margarine.
Stir to form a thin dough; pour evenly over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour until crust rises to top and browns lightly.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Stir in oil, almond extract and sugar until mixture thickens.
Add the flour and mix well.
Drop teaspoon size amounts of batter on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Cream oleo, eggs, sugar, honey, vanilla and peanut butter. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix and spread in greased pan; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: In blender, process the beef, eggs and onions.
Add pickles and mayonnaise.
Good on crackers and for finger sandwiches.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef in skillet with chopped onion until meat is gray. Add beans, soup and chili powder to mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
May add a little water to soup if thin is desired.

title: quick breakfast ring
directions: Shape biscuits into balls.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll each ball in melted butter, then in sugar-cinnamon-nut mixture.
Arrange balls in bottom of an 8 1/4-inch well-greased ring mold, leaving about 1/4-inch between each.
Make a second layer, placing the balls over the spaces.
Bake in 450° oven for about 15 minutes or until done.
Turn out on plate immediately and decorate top with a thin powdered sugar frosting and candied cherries, if desired.
Serve piping hot.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cook together milk, sugar, and egg yolks until it boils.
Add lemon jello; let stand until it starts to set.
Add pineapple, egg whites and heavy cream, prepared Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Line bottom of long pan with angel food cake slices.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over cake then add another layer of cake slices.
Pour the rest of the mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy zucchini jelly
directions: Boil zucchini in water until almost clear.
Add sugar and boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add gelatin and pineapple.
Pour into glass container and refrigerate.
Makes 13 cups.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Add scalded milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bread cubes and raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-buttered 6-cup baking dish.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix the top 3 ingredients together with the dry onion soup mix.
Put in dish and pour mushroom soup and water over it.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, vanilla and melted margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Make batter with ingredients and pour half into a 9-inch greased iron skillet. Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese over batter. Cover with rest of batter. Bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add mashed bananas.
Fold in nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans or 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: chicken breast
directions: Debone and pound breasts.
Inside each piece, roll a piece of dried beef, jelly roll fashion.
Wrap with a strip of bacon. Cover bottom of casserole with dried beef.
Lay chicken on top of dried beef.
Pour sour cream and soup over the chicken.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Sprinkle toasted almonds over chicken.
Serve over wild rice.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the above and pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 box of dry yellow cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 cup of chopped pecans over cake mix and bake another 30 minutes.

title: fettucine geraldo
directions: Boil egg noodles until "almost done" in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Drain off water.
Add butter or margarine and stir gently until melted; add heavy cream; add cheeses and stir gently over very low heat until melted (adjust cheese to taste).

title: cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened margarine or butter with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add to batter.
Blend well. Drop cookies from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Garnish casserole with drained asparagus spears and pimento strips, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Beat ingredients for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped milk.
Pour in a crust which consists of 1/2 stick margarine, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour, salt and milk together. Cook until slightly thickened. Pour 1/2 cup hot chocolate mixture into beaten egg yolks and return to mixture to thicken. Add vanilla and butter and let cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Line a large baking pan with stale bread; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Pour over bread, slowly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until no milk shows on top.
Remove and let cool before cutting.

title: stuffed cucumbers from france
directions: Scratch the sides of cucumbers lengthwise with a fork to make grooves.
Cut each cucumber into 1-inch thick slices.
Hollow each slice halfway through.
Combine radishes with carrots, parsley, dill and crab.
Combine mayo with sour cream.
Add to the salad and season.
Stuff cucumber slices with the mixture.
Place a tomato half at the center of each stuffed cucumber slice.

title: apple nut coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add 1 cup flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sour cream and mix well; then add second cup flour and mix.
Fold in chopped apples and spread in greased 13 x 9 pan.
Mix nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cooking oil together.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed meat roll
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Put on waxed paper. Pat out in sheet 14-inches long x 10-inches wide.

title: delma's spinach dip
directions: Squeeze water out of thawed spinach. Combine and mix all ingredients. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving. Best if made and refrigerated overnight.

title: easy fettuccine(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in skillet until golden; stir in cheese (cubed), milk and Parmesan until melted.
Add to fettuccine and serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop garlic and onion.	Saute in a small amount of oil. Add rice
and
stir
for
a few minutes to pick up the flavor. Add saffron, consomme, water, pimientos and mushrooms.	Bring to a boil and bake covered in a 10-inch Dutch oven for 1 hour over medium heat.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook chicken in kettle with water, bouillon cubes, minced garlic, chopped celery, onion, parsley, pinch of basil, salt and pepper.
Strain broth and cook noodles in half broth and half water.
When done, drain and set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put 1 cup of berries in 2 cup measuring cup.
Crush.
Fill cup with cold water. Put in a pan.
Add sugar and bring to a boil. Add cornstarch mixed in a little water.
Cook until thick.
Add strawberry jello and lemon juice.
Cool.
Have baked crust ready. Slice rest of strawberries.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherries and pineapple (mixed) in buttered baking pan. Put dry cake mix on top.
Put butter pats all over top of this. Bake at 350° until crust is browned.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Grate cucumber (remove seeds) and onion. (Do not use juice from cucumber and onion.)
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add enough sour cream to make it creamy for dip.

title: spicy fried chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a small bowl, combine pepper, poultry seasoning, paprika, cayenne pepper and dry mustard.
Rub mixture on chicken.
Coat evenly using all of the spices.
Rub in a paper or plastic bag. Combine flour, salt, garlic powder and celery salt.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Shake to coat.

title: chicken and wheat berry bake
directions: *Can be purchased at health food shops.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls as directed.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix; spread over baked rolls.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
(Rolls should be spread and pressed as a pizza on a large pizza pan.)

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool, then place topping on top.

title: double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2 inches).
In large mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
(Top may appear wet.)
Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Cream Layer on cake.
Chill.
Pour Chocolate Topping over dessert.
Cover; chill.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and stir.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts; stir.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
They are out of this world.

title: blueberry or cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix heated butter and graham cracker crumbs together for crust.
Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese into bowl #1.
In bowl #2, mix half and half and Dream Whip.
Beat.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with their skins on.
When done, skin potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Add chopped onions, Dijon mustard, salad oil, wine vinegar, parsley and hard boiled egg (grated) and toss lightly.

title: dijon-glazed chicken
directions: Place the chicken in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish coated with cooking spray.
Brush glaze (first 4 ingredients mixed together) over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Uncover and broil chicken 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.

title: busy day apple turnovers
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and cinnamon in a saucepan; heat until hot.
Roll out biscuits, one at a time.
Put a heaping tablespoonful of apple mixture in the center; fold over and seal edges.
Drop in hot fat and fry until brown on both sides.
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: In saucepan, cook cauliflower covered in half the chicken broth for 5 to 8 minutes until tender.
In saucepan, combine remaining chicken broth, broccoli and dill weed.
Cook, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Remove from heat; place cauliflower mixture in blender.
Cover until smooth.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Add milk all at once and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir sauce, cauliflower
mix and cheese into broccoli mixture; cook and stir until heated and cheese is melted.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion in oil or shortening of choice. Boil rice, drain and rinse. Combine beans, sauteed onion, cooked rice and cumin in casserole dish. Place in 300 degree oven and cook for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate coke cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Put aside in bowl.

title: chicken tikka(curried chicken grilled)
directions: Skin, bone and grind chicken.
Debone chicken and discard all but meat of chicken.
Discard wings.
Chop meat up and grind if possible.
Combine chicken, bread crumbs, onions, tomatoes, coriander, ginger, garlic, garam masala, cumin, red pepper, salt and egg in deep bowl.
Mix well in bowl.
Divide into 8 equal parts in pan.
Heat oil in pan and deep fry chicken mixture to form cutlets.
Fry on each side until brown.

title: hot spinach crabmeat dip
directions: Press Ricotta cheese through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl.
Add skim milk, mayo and sherry; stir well.
Drain spinach; press between paper towels to remove moisture.
Add spinach, chestnuts, crab, cheese, red peppers, onions and hot sauce to cheese mixture.
Stir well.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In a coated skillet, combine ground turkey, onions, celery and brown together.
Drain mixture.
Add all seasonings and supplements and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and add cabbage and mushrooms.
Simmer until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: mama lucy's quick candy
directions: Sift powdered sugar and set aside.

In a heavy skillet over low heat mix cocoa, butter and peanut butter until melted. Remove from heat and add alternately powdered sugar and coffee; mix well using as little coffee as needed to make a stiff mixture. Gradually add crushed crackers and mix well.
Pour into greased deep pie dish.
Chill well before slicing to serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple crisp
directions: Layer apples in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients. Add eggs and mix until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Pour 2/3 cup of melted and cooled butter-flavored Crisco over topping.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (my Mom did this by hand, yuk). Spread in ungreased loaf pans (2), 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Pour off fat carefully after about 1 hour.)
Serve with purchased gravy.
Makes enough for company and Shepherd's Pie the next night.

title: scotch scones
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add shortening and mix in very lightly.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour slowly into flour mixture.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares and fold over into 3-cornered pieces.
Place in greased baking pan and brush with milk.
Dust with sugar.
Bake 20 minutes in hot oven.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until it loses redness.
Drain fat. Stir in macaroni, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until onion is transparent.
Add Hunt's sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir.
Let stand 5 minutes with heat off.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat bacon over medium heat; add onion, pepper and garlic and cook until transparent and tender.
Add and mix well the catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, mustard and pepper.
Drain beans and toss lightly with sauce.
Place in casserole and bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: tomato-mozzarella salad
directions: Mix vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Slowly pour in oil, stirring constantly with fork until well blended.
Add tomatoes, cheese, onion and basil; toss to mix.
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 days.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli-mushroom spaghetti
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package (or steam fresh); drain. Stir in mushrooms, margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are hot, about 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Mix broccoli and mushroom mixture.
Toss with spaghetti, low-fat cheese and lemon juice.
If desired, top with additional Parmesan and Romano low-fat grated cheeses.
Serves 5.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir together spaghetti, butter, parmesan cheese and eggs. Press into 10-inch or larger pie plate to make a crust.
Fry hamburger, onion & pepper and drain.
Add cheddar cheese, then the sauce; stir to mix and pour into spaghetti pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 min.
Add mozzarella cheese and bake 10 min. more.
Let stand for 10 min. to set.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with 2/3 can of Campbell's soup.
Add chopped onion.
Mix well. Chill for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Make patty to desired size.
Bread patty with bread crumbs, then fry in vegetable oil until golden brown on both sides.
With remainder of soup, heat and pour over tuna cakes, if desired.
(Do not add milk or water to the soup.)

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Blend together all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Spread batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in pot.
Add tomatoes, corn and its liquid, rice and taco seasoning.
Simmer until rice is cooked.
Spoon mixture into Pyrex dish(es).
Sprinkle with grated cheese and heat in microwave or conventional oven.
Set your table with a bowl of sour cream and another of taco sauce.

title: mozzarella with artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts and water chestnuts.
Then combine all ingredients in an oven or microwave-proof 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Microwave on High 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with cocktail bread or crackers.

title: do-ahead relish
directions: Drain the corn, beans and peas.
Mix with celery, bell pepper, onion and pimiento.
Combine sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil. Cool.
Add oil and mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Can be used as a vegetable, salad or with other relish items.
Will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix cake mix, 3/4 cup milk and margarine; spoon half the batter into the pan.
Bake for 6 minutes, or until it starts to get firm.
Melt caramels with the remaining milk.
Remove cake from oven.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spoon caramel over chips and nuts.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Top with remaining chips and nuts.
Return to oven; bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool before cutting.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll dough onto floured surface; cut biscuits out and bake at 425° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini minestrone soup
directions: Add oil to heated pot and heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium-low heat until onion is soft.
Add celery, carrots, zucchini, tomatoes, chickpeas, water and salt and pepper.
Mix gently.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and boil gently, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add pasta to boiling soup. Cover and boil gently until pasta is tender, but still firm, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley and basil.

title: mexican tortilla bake
directions: In a skillet, brown ground meat and drain off any grease or liquid.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on to meat.
Pour in picante sauce and Velveeta.
Stir until cheese is melted and mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture and blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough in a ball and chill 15 minutes.
Makes 2 double crust 9-inch pies and 1 (9-inch) shell.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain the grease.
Add taco seasoning and prepare according to package directions.
Let cool. Spread sour cream in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Next, layer the meat, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onions (optional).
Serve with your favorite taco sauce and dip with nachos.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix egg and sugars; add remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Top with whipped cream or serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large warm bowl (not too warm, room temperature; no cold draft).
Heat in a saucepan the water, milk and oil until very warm to touch.
Add to flour, etc. in bowl.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl.
Blend in 3/4 cup more flour at low speed. Beat at high for 3 minutes.
It will start to get sticky.
Stir in remaining 2 3/4 cups flour.
Will make soft dough.

title: pastrami pickle roll-ups
directions: Drain and dry pickles with a napkin.
Cover pickles with cream cheese.
Roll covered pickle up with a slice of pastrami.
Hold meat on pickle by putting toothpicks through pickle.
The size of the pickles will determine how many toothpicks are used.
Slice between toothpicks.
There you have appetizers already on picks, ready to eat.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Combine pineapple, cranberries, Cool Whip and nuts and mix together.
Stir in Jell-O that has been cooled. Pour into a square glass baking dish, freeze, cut into squares and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.
Delicious.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, 2/3 of Cool Whip and 10x sugar well and spread over crust.
Beat pudding mix and cold milk and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1/3 of Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with chopped nut meats.
Refrigerate.

title: herbed cream cheese appetizers
directions: Thaw pastry sheets at room temperature for about 20 minutes before unfolding.
Place each rectangle on lightly floured board. Cut out about 24 - 2 1/2 inch rounds with biscuit cutter.

title: chicken with prosciutto and provolone cheese
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
With a sharp pointed knife, make a pocket on each of the 4 pieces of chicken.
Wrap each piece of cheese with a slice of Prosciutto.
Insert into pockets and secure with a toothpick.
Brush with oil, then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, on each side.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart saucepan, brown beef with onion and garlic. Remove any grease.
Add tomato sauce, cream of mushroom soup and rest of ingredients except sour cream; mix well.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper; reheat, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles (the wide ribbon ones).
Freeze any leftovers for another meal.
Serves 8.

title: german pork and celery stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine water, chicken bouillon granules and cornstarch until smooth; set aside.
In a wok or large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil until hot.
Add celery, sweet red pepper and onion; cook and stir four minutes or until vegetables are nearly crisp-tender.
Remove; set aside, but keep warm.
Add remaining oil; add pork.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes or until pork is no longer pink.
Stir in reserved cornstarch mixture, Worcestershire sauce, caraway seed, salt and pepper; bring mixture to boiling. Stir in apples and vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in a large container.
Chill for 24 hours.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: chicken flauntas
directions: In saucepan, melt oleo; stir in flour and salt.
Add chicken broth, cook until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Add lemon juice, parsley, onion, pepper, nutmeg and paprika.
Stir in chicken.
Cool slightly to soften tortillas.
Dip in hot oil for a few seconds or until limp.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of chicken mixture over each tortilla.
Roll up tightly and secure each roll with wooden toothpicks.

title: gem jams
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put dabs of dough on pan, then some filling, then finish with a small dab of dough on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Let cook on tray for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: jell-o poke cake
directions: Prick cake with large two pronged fork at 1/2 inch intervals. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake layers.
Chill 4 hours.
Mix Cool Whip and thawed strawberries.
Frost cake and garnish with sliced fresh strawberries.

title: hot peppers and hot dogs
