directions: Bring sugar, oil, vinegar and ketchup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Seed and chop peppers into large pieces.
Add peppers to ketchup mixture.
Cook until fork tender.
(Do not overcook). Cut hot dogs into large pieces and add to mixture.	Puts into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 15 pints.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put cocoa, sugar, butter and flour in pan.
Stir in milk and 2 egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put meringue on top and brown.

title: icy orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; mix together.
Sprinkle dry orange jello over that.
Fold in the cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: late supper salad
directions: Combine tuna fish, macaroni, peas, celery and chopped eggs. Add onion juice and salt and pickles.
Blend well with enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill thoroughly and serve on crisp lettuce nest.
Garnish with paprika.

title: velma's white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten yolks and extract.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit. Last add beaten egg whites.
Grease and line pan of choice with brown paper.
This will make one tube cake or two loaf cakes.
Bake 2 hours at 250° if baked in loaf pan.
Will take longer in tube pan, probably about 5 hours.

title: drop noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl until blended into a stiff dough. Drop by teaspoons in pot of boiling, salted water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain into cold water.
Drain again.

title: green chile
directions: Cube pork roast in 1/2-inch pieces.
Leave fat on.
Brown cubed pork with one chopped onion.
Add flour and brown.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil and then add chili powder, cumin, cilantro, garlic, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to simmer and add 1 onion, all chilies and tomatoes.
Simmer one hour.

title: crusty chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and melted butter.
Dip the chicken breasts into the mixture and roll in stuffing.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered for an additional 25 minutes.

title: double chocolates
directions: Combine and mix the first 5 ingredients. Add water and blend well. Fold in 2/3 cup chocolate morsels and 2/3 cup pecans. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet and lightly flatten by crisscrossing with damp fork.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature. Yields 4 dozen.
After cookies are baked and well cooled, top with pecan half, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In well buttered 2 qt. casserole arrange in alternate layers potatoes, onions and salt.
Repeat 3 times.
In a saucepan heat soup, milk and worcestershire sauce.
Pour over potato mixture. Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water for 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients together and cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken livers and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until brown.
Add livers and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Wash rice well and add 4 cups water. Boil 10 minutes.
Add chicken livers to rice.
Simmer covered until rice is done.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: black bean tortilla casserole
directions: Combine onion, peppers, tomatoes, picante sauce and cumin in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, put 1/3 of the bean/tomato mixture.
Top with half of the tortillas and then half of the cheese.
I slice up some black olives and top the cheese with them.
Next, spread 1/3 bean mixture, top with remaining tortillas and then remaining bean mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top, let stand for 10 minutes.
If you like, you can then top the casserole with lettuce, tomato, black olives, sour cream, etc.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In ovenproof dish, cook sausage until lightly brown.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in rice, broth, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Fluff lightly with fork.
Remove bay leaf.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Chop bacon in small pieces.
Cook in large pan or skillet. Drain excess grease and save.
Cook bacon, but not crisp.
Chop ham into small pieces.
Chop green onion tops into small pieces. Add to bacon that's already cooked.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs slightly with hand beater; beat in remaining ingredients.
Place pastry lined pie plate on oven rack.
Pour in filling.
Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean; refrigerate.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining pie immediately. Makes 6 servings, 440 calories per serving.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and bake at 500° for 30 minutes. Take this and crumble real good with the biscuits. Then mix sage, salt and pepper real good. Add eggs and onion. Pour chicken broth over this until the consistency you want. Bake at 450° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In saucepan, combine
sugar,
evaporated milk, cinnamon and butter;
bring to rolling boil over medium-high flame and boil
1 minute.
Stir in vanilla, salt and pecan halves.
Pour onto lightly
buttered baking sheet.
Cool and separate pecan halves. Makes 2 to 3 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all, except butter and vanilla, in a heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into prebaked pie crust.
Top with meringue or sprinkle with 1 (7 ounce) bag chocolate covered peanuts (chopped).

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Grate potatoes and add all other ingredients.
Put into greased baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy basic dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Stuffs 12 to 14 pound turkey or bake in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carnival jambalaya
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
a
large	skillet.
Cover skillet and bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pudding
directions: Combine together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes a breadlike topping.
A meal in itself.

title: duckie's raw apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix apples and nuts.
Combine oil, eggs and vanilla and add to apples and nuts.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture.
Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in an 8-inch pan.
Cool. Place cake layers, top side up, in two clean 8-inch pans.
Poke each cake with a fork in 1/2 inch intervals on the first layer. Top the top and sides with Cool Whip.
Garnish and decorate, if desired.

title: apple brandy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray or grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 13 x 9 lightly greased pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: cindy's apple chip cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend dry ingredients together and add to mix, mixing well.
Then add vanilla and mix well. Stir in white chocolate chips and diced apples.
Pour into lightly greased bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: flapper girl salad
directions: Drain pineapple and spread 1/2 wafer crumbs on bottom of dish. Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites.
Beat all together; fold in pineapple and chopped nuts.
Pour mixture over wafer crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate 5 hours or overnight.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 2 quart casserole dish.
Wash and peel eggplant.
Cut into 2-inch cubes.
Simmer covered in small amount of water (salted) for 10 minutes.
Drain. Meanwhile, in hot oil skillet, saute garlic until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, tomatoes, salt, sugar, paprika, pepper and basil.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until mixture boils and is slightly thickened.
In prepared casserole, layer eggplant alternately with tomato mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until top is slightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: all conference hamburger dip
directions: Saute ground beef until brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: chicken fajitas (1)
directions: Season chicken breasts with seasoning and let cool in fridge for about 2 hours.
Grill either on the Bar-B-Que or in a skillet. Fry onions and peppers in a separate skillet.
Slice chicken when done and combine with onions and peppers.
Serve with your favorite rice and beans.

title: quick crescent loaf
directions: Brown meat and onions and drain off fat.
Add Worcestershire sauce and soup; mix well and let cool a little.
Place crescent rolls out flat with long sides to middle.
Put meat mixture in middle and wrap sides around the meat to form a loaf.
Top with cheese and cook at 350° until brown.

title: tomato and broccoli toss
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, except use a large saucepan and 4 cups hot water.
Drain.

title: tacos and black beans
directions: Open cans of black beans into a saucepan and add a little salt and pepper.
Put on low heat.
In a frypan, chop bell pepper, onions and bacon.
Saute.
Drain and put in the black beans and continue on low heat.
Clean frypan and brown hamburger.
Drain the hamburger and follow directions on taco seasoning.
While that is cooking, cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Shred cheese and chop or slice lettuce.
Place taco shells in a 9 x 13-inch pan with 3 to 4 shells each row.

title: pumpkin-pecan biscuits(12 to 16 biscuits)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles small peas.
Stir in pecans.
In a glass measuring up, combine pumpkin and half and half.
Stir into flour mixture.
Dough should be stiff.

title: spam or ham casserole
directions: Mix
ground
Spam
or
Ham,
chicken noodle soup, oats, eggs, evaporated milk, pepper, onion and seasonings together. Place in a 9	x
13-inch
greased
pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Remove from
oven and top with undiluted cream of mushroom soup and cheese.
Bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 layers or loaf cake.
Grease and flour pans.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions for 20 minutes in water at a slow simmer.
Add carrots and celery; cook 20 minutes more.
Add herbs.
Make a roux of flour and butter; add to soup.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apricot jello supreme
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Cut cream cheese in pieces and add to jello while hot.
Beat with beater.
Set until it reaches a liver stage, then mix in undrained fruit and fold in Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla and egg and beat well. Stir in flour and oats; blend.
Spread in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Spread chocolate bits over; when melted, spread with a spatula.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: governor's casserole
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into florets and parboil for 5 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour and blend well.
Gradually add milk and stir until thickened. Add cheeses and stir until melted.
Place vegetables in 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with ham.
Pour cheese sauce over all. Put buttered crumbs around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hurry-up chicken
directions: Mix soup mix, sugar, ketchup and water; pour over chicken. Bake for 1 hour or until tender at 350° to 375°.

title: granville gilbert's "world's greatest cookie"(served at the 1994 christmas house tour)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well.
Add salad oil, mixing well.
Add oats, corn flakes, nuts and coconut, stirring well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and add vanilla.

title: janis' chicken macaroni salad
directions: Chop the green onions, bell pepper and celery and put into a large bowl.
Chop up the boiled chicken breasts and add to the vegetables.
Add the noodles, Miracle Whip, mustard honey mayonnaise and 1/2 bottle of creamy Italian salad dressing.
Put a lid on your bowl and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, add the other 1/2 bottle salad dressing and mix well.

title: low-fat raisin nut muffin
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and honey to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until done.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Cook beef in oil.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, mustard and oregano.
Mix well.
Stir in macaroni.
Cover and simmer to blend flavors about 20 to 25 minutes.
Just before serving, add Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine (melted), 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Beat together egg whites, margarine and remaining powdered sugar for 10 minutes and spread over first layer.
Lay bananas on top of second layer.
Cover with pineapple.
Spread dairy topping over this.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Beat all cake ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: make-ahead breakfast
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Line croutons on bottom. Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Brown sausage.
Cut into pieces and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt in small bowl.
Pour over croutons and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, dilute mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Top should be lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut, pecans and pineapple.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine vegetable oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Place paper baking cups in muffin pans.
Spoon batter into paper cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and egg.
Pour over melted margarine.
Top with fruit.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding banana cream mix with milk according to package directions.
Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding to make 3 layers of each, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Spoon on top of pudding, spreading to cover entire surface.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Crush crackers and spread on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Cut in half.
Put half into bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Put 1 box of pudding on cake.
Put 1 can strawberries on pudding.
Put 1 carton Cool Whip on strawberries.
Repeat with cake, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: russian tea
directions: Steep tea in boiling water. Strain. Add spices, juice and peels.
Add sugar.
Let set for awhile. Remove spices and peels. Strain.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Parboil bell peppers (cut off tops and reserve edge flesh to dice) approximately 10 minutes.
Cook rice.
Mix meat, diced onion, diced bell pepper tops, tomatoes, cooked rice, egg and seasonings with hands (mush up good).
Spoon into bell pepper shells and place in deep baking dish; cover with tomato sauce (diluted with 1/2 can water).
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Preheat
oven
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick. In
a 1
1/2-quart
casserole, alternately layer potatoes and apples, ending
with
potatoes and sprinkling each layer with some	of sugar, allspice, butter and lemon juice.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Serves 8.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Thaw the Cool Whip, then mix together with the other ingredients.
Let chill.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package direction; drain well and set aside.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large saucepan.
Add cranberry sauce and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold (lightly greased with mayonnaise) and refrigerate.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Follow directions on box of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
With fork, punch holes in cake.
Pour cream of coconut on cake.
Mix condensed milk, crushed pineapple and lemon juice; spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Keep in fridge.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix soup, 1/2 cup cheese, pimiento, salt and mushrooms.
Gradually stir in milk and potatoes.
Put in greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake in a 350° (moderate) oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatballs parmesan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with hamburger.
Form into 24 meatballs.
Cook in skillet 15 minutes, turning, until browned all over.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Drain and put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Evenly cover noodles with meatball sauce and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: santa's elves holiday treat
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter; press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and the 1 cup butter 8 to 10 minutes (makes it fluffy).
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Spread over crust and arrange bananas over top; sprinkle with coconut.
Spread dessert topping over all; sprinkle with nuts.
Cover; chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
Garnish each serving with a candy cane and banana slices.
Makes 12 servings.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs. Blend sugar and flour. Stir in eggs. Add coconut and vanilla. Put in 2 (9-inch) greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until coconut is brown and pie is firm.

title: lee ann la claux's apple crisp
directions: Fill a 9 x 13-inch pan with apples, peeled, cored and sliced. Sprinkle with first 4 ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes until apples are tender.
While apples are baking, mix Bisquick, white and brown sugars and vanilla.
Work in margarine until crumbly.
When apples are tender, cover with topping. Bake another 15 minutes without foil cover.

title: communion bread
directions: This bread can be marked with a 5-tined fork symbolic of the five wounds of Jesus.
It can also be eaten as a treat or with soup.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all the vegetables and pimento.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: texas cake
directions: In large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, eggs and sour cream.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil water, butter and cocoa.
Add this to the flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecuing on herbed charcoal
directions: Add thyme or marjoram to hot charcoal.
The herbed charcoal will lend a delicious flavor to a variety of meats, such as chicken or fish.
Grill prepared meat and serve immediately.

title: baked flounder supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 5 custard cups with aluminum foil. Set on baking sheet.
Cut fillets into long strips.
On piece of waxed paper, combine crumbs, salt and pepper.
Coat fish with crumbs. Dip in egg mixture.
Coat again with crumbs.
Lay flat on table.
Spread fish with crab meat.
Roll up each strip like a jelly roll.
Secure with wooden picks.
Place pat of butter or margarine in each cup.
Place fish roll on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in a preheated oven for 20 minutes.

title: go to bed mints
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar; add sugar, salt and coloring to form stiff peaks.
Then add chips, chopped dried fruits or nuts.
Put by teaspoons on foiled cookie sheets and place in preheated 375° oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Fill a 5 gallon gumbo pot half full with water.
Heat water, but don't boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Salt and pepper chicken and fry in a small amount of oil.
With fresh oil, fry half of the hot Italian sausage.
Do the same for half of smoked sausage.
(Save the other half of the sausage to be added to the gumbo later.)
Save the oil in separate containers.
It may be used later to add flavor to the gumbo.
Pour a little of the chicken oil in your pot (not too much or it will be greasy).
Add the veal, beef, ham, beef franks and sausage.
Clean the crabs.
Break them in half.
Pull off the claws.
Put the claws in the pot.
Then lightly fry, almost saute, half of the crabs.
Put the other half in the pot.
(Tomato paste is optional.
Traditionally it is not used.
Add after crabs.)
Let simmer for an hour to let flavors blend.
Add more water if needed.
Meat should float in water as in a soup.
Add shrimp.
Let cook for another half hour.
Add oysters 10 minutes before serving.
Add file immediately before serving, unless you plan to save some of the gumbo for later.
If so, let everyone sprinkle the file in his or her bowl.
Serve over rice with a mustard style mashed potato salad as a side dish.

title: applesauce oat bran muffins
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy. Add applesauce and raisins; mix well. Combine oat bran, flour and cinnamon in bowl. Add applesauce mixture. Mix just until moistened. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: pancakes(m. mouse, mr. smiley and silver dollars)
directions: Beat until blended. Bake on hot greased griddle.

title: french toast
directions: Break eggs into a shallow dish.
Beat with fork lightly.
Stir in salt, sugar and milk.
Heat a little butter in a skillet.
Dip bread slices into mixture, both sides.
Brown both sides.
Serve with syrup.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo or Pam.
Cook at medium heat until onions are transparent; add soup and heat well.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses and stir well.
Add rest of ingredients except crackers.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture in pan, then put crackers on top and dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except raisins. Mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Store in a cool, dry place or in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and season with diced onions or onion salt. Add soup and corn.
Simmer potatoes until done and add to mixture. Real good on mashed potatoes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salsa in a pan over medium heat. Stir until cream cheese is melted. Once cream cheese is melted, add can of chili. Stir until mixture is warm and serve with chips.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Saute onion in half the butter over low heat.
Melt rest of the butter in top of double boiler and blend in the flour.
Stir in the onion and add 1 quart milk, stirring constantly.
Add the crab meat and roe and stir well; add pepper and mace and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add the pint of milk and stir well.
Remove from heat and add wine.
Serve in soup bowls which have been heated, top with a dollop of cream and garnish with parsley sprigs or a sprinkle of paprika.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream, soup
broth
and chilies.
Heat and stir until smooth and well blended.
To soften tortillas, heat a small amount of reserved	chicken broth in a skillet.
Place tortillas, one at a time,
in broth for a few seconds.
Remove and drain. After draining,
place
tortillas one at time into soup mixture. Lift tortillas out	of
soup and place 3 tablespoons chicken and 2 to	3 tablespoons cheese in the center of each tortilla.
Roll
up and place, seam side down, in 2-quart baking dish.	Pour remaining
sauce over.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook hamburg in large frying pan.
Drain fat.
Saute garlic, green pepper and onion.
Add tomato, chili sauce, seasonings and a little water for the right consistency.
Cook macaroni and add to hamburg mixture.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cook in a 325° oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Add water and butter to soups; heat until butter melts.
Add rice.
Pour half in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put chicken on top, then pour rest of liquid on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: wendy's scallop-bacon wrap
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash scallops thoroughly.
Place in colander to drain, then put into a medium bowl.
Sprinkle Goya seasoning over scallops and mix by hand to distribute it evenly. Cut the bacon strips in half.
Beat eggs well in small bowl.
Put bread crumbs in another bowl.
Wrap half a bacon strip around each scallop.
Then dip in egg, and shake off excess.
Roll in crumbs and place in shallow casserole.
Cut butter into bits and distribute evenly over scallops.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes. Then run casserole under broiler for 5 to 7 minutes until bacon is golden-crisp.

title: pumpkin streusel cake
directions: Heat
oven
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9
x
2-inches.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside. Mix
cake
mix,
water,
eggs, pumpkin, flour, oil and baking soda
in
large
bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly about
seconds.
Then
beat on medium speed until completely mixed.
Spread
half of the batter in cake pan and sprinkle
with half of brown sugar mixture.
Bake about 35 to 40
minutes
or until
wooden toothpick inserted in center of cake comes
out clean.
Can be served alone or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Spread into greased pan.
Mix together brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over all and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Good with ice cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts and then coconut on bottom.
Prepare cake mix as instructed on box.
Melt margarine and then mix into cream cheese.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Then dribble cream cheese and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Put Cool Whip on top as you serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam (9 x 13-inch) and flour.
Spread on bottom coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix oleo, Philly cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minute or until you pull out a clean toothpick as you are testing.
Serve out of baking dish.
Looks like and earthquake, but delicious!

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in hot water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until clear, thick and smooth.
Add vanilla and butter.
Serve warm over pound cake.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Wash meat in cold water.
Cover pan with Reynolds Wrap.
Place brisket in pan, fat side up.
Cover with celery and onion. Sprinkle paprika on top until brisket is red in color.
Seal in Reynolds Wrap.
Pour 1 cup water in bottom of pan.
Bake at 250° for about 4 hours.

title: texas stew
directions: Trim pork of all fat.
Place in a large saucepan with onion and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Refrigerate and skim off any congealed fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with jalapeno cornbread wedges.

title: cinderella's cake
directions: Mix oats and water; let stand until cool.
Stir together next 4 ingredients.
In large bowl, stir margarine and sugar until blended; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; add flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in oatmeal.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° moderate oven 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Spread with Quick Topping while cake is warm.

title: slushy punch
directions: Make jello according to package instructions; mix with other ingredients.
Put in 2 gallon Tupperware bucket with cover.
Place in deep freeze, stirring occasionally, until slushy, about a day.

title: brownies (double making)
directions: Dump and mix.
Bake in 300° oven until a toothpick comes out clean.
Please do not overbake this original recipe.

title: sweet potato browns
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts. Add potatoes, apple and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar, allspice and apple juice; cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until potato is tender.
Serve immediately.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and crumble. Mix tomatoes, green onions, celery, bell pepper and pickles. Set aside. Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice. Layer cornbread, vegetables and mayonnaise in large bowl.

title: bacon, cheese and tomato loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat bread according to package directions; split loaf lengthwise.
Place loaf halves, split side up on cookie sheet.
To assemble, sandwich layer each half evenly with tomato, basil, cheese and bacon.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add pineapple-grapefruit juice; chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add the chilled ginger ale.
Yield:
About 32 punch cup servings.

title: additions and garnishes
directions: Clear Soups:
Crisp whole wheat crackers, cheese pastry, cheese-spread toast strips.

title: bailey's irish cream mousse
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; let stand in pan 5 minutes. Combine sugar, yolks and Bailey's and blend in chocolate mixture. Whip cream and fold into chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks and fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into serving dish and chill.
Garnish with shaved chocolate, if desired. Serves 8 to 10.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk until well blended and begins to thicken.
Cook for 1 minute after it starts to boil. Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oats; blend well.
Work fast, as this mixture hardens fast.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: quick canned soup with a zest!!!
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; heat to simmering.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients at medium speed until blended. Reserve 1 cup of batter.
Spread remaining batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk in a heavy saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.

title: date nut cake
directions: Chip pecans and dates.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and pinch of salt, then add eggs and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook whole potatoes with peelings.
When soft (sharp knife will go through), drain and peel.
Slice round and thin; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley and sliced eggs.
Add enough oil until it doesn't look dry.
Add vinegar and mustard.
Dissolve a bouillon cube in water.
Add this last.
Mix all together.

title: cinnamon crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add molasses, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs to creamed mixture.
Beat to blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press cookies flat, approximately 1 1/2 inches across.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Add cake mix, sour cream, eggs and liqueur. Mix together. Add slowly the chocolate chips and almond brickle. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour in Bundt pan. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes in pan, then cool out of pan on wire rack. Top with whip cream, if desired.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix together. Drop spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.

title: duck soup chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well; pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ginger ale. Add it right before your going to serve. Makes 4 gallons.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, water, corn syrup, cinnamon, cloves and ginger in a saucepan.
Place over moderate heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add margarine and stir until cool. Dissolve baking soda in 1 tablespoon water and add to mixture.
Add flour gradually and work until dough is firm.
Form cookies using a mold or roll and use cookie cutters. Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: summertime iced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water about 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; drain.
Place cooked broccoli in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Boil chicken until cooked; drain. Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together.
Spread over top of chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over all. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: potluck potato dish
directions: Mix last four ingredients; stir in potatoes.
Top with potato chips, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: granola
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix brown sugar, oil and water together and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix to coat evenly.

title: slow-cooker pork and apple curry
directions: In a 3-quart slow cooker, combine the first 10 ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender. Increase heat to high. In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water until smooth; stir into slow cooker. Cover and cook for 30 minutes or until thickened, stirring once. Serve over rice, if desired. Sprinkle with raisins and coconut. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with electric mixer.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together.
Shape in loaf and bake 1 1/4 hours in 350 degree oven.

title: sausage and sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain and peel.
Mash and beat well, adding all ingredients and enough cream to make mixture light and fluffy.
Pour into casserole and press sausages into surface.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until sausages are brown.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add unbeaten eggs, melted butter, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in chopped apples. Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: blitzer candy
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and milk until smooth.
Add nuts; shape into balls.
Chill!
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture and place on tray to set!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand mixer.
Spoon mixture into 3 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done in center.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: martha's cranberry casserole(serve with turkey or chicken in place of cranberry sauce.)
directions: Adjust sugar to your family taste.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt the butter; add brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: 2-minute pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a baked pie shell. Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut over filling and add any desirable decoration.
So easy...so good!

title: quick peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup, then microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Mix in peanuts and microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes more.
Mix in butter and vanilla and microwave 1 minute more. Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda (it will be foamy). Carefully pour hot brittle onto cookie sheet (let a grownup do this).
Spread brittle and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 4 tablespoons butter; melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of cake pan, 9 inches round by 3 inches deep.
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, combine the first five ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Remove bone from stock and cut off meat.
Return meat to the kettle.

title: spiced granola
directions: Combine oats, coconut, pecans, wheat germ, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl; mix well.
Add honey and oil; mix well.
Spread in 2 (10 x 15-inch) baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Add raisins and mix well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Crumble 1/2 box crackers.
Cut 1/2 stick margarine in small pieces and place evenly over crackers. Layer chicken and chestnuts over crackers.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of shallow dish.	Spread tuna over cream cheese.	Pour cocktail sauce over tuna.	Spread on your favorite crackers.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Mix and do by each step listed in order.
Set until it starts to gel.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped cream.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Roll mixture of beef, egg, crumbs, salt, pepper and onion into little balls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs and beat together for 4 minutes.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda into sugar mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and stir into mixture until well blended.
Use an ice cream scoop or large spoon to place dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen large cookies.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In oblong baking dish, add milk, eggs, pepper and cheese. Mix well and add cooked macaroni. Sprinkle a small amount of black pepper over top and bake in 350° oven until cheese and mixture are done.

title: garden dip
directions: I put green onions, radishes, cucumbers and bell pepper in food chopper.
Add sour cream and Miracle Whip.

title: low-fat herbed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Dry well.
Do not peel.
Line baking pan with foil and spray.
Cut potatoes into 6 wedges.
Place potatoes, skin side down, and spray lightly with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with Recipe Secret onion soup mix or your favorite spices.
Bake at 400° until fork-tender, about 25 minutes.

title: mary ella paige's apple frosting
directions: Combine in a 1-quart bowl and beat on 3/4 speed until stiff. If no beater is available, a fork may be used, with the ingredients on a pie plate.
This takes about 20 minutes or until the fork will stand upright in the piled up frosting.
Will frost a 2 layer cake and should be eaten the same day it is made.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, egg and celery; mix in remaining ingredients, plus a dash of salt and pepper.
Chill.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat together oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Then add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Pour in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake according to package directions.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, until smooth.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and mix well.
Roll dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies or 10 to 12 minutes for crispier cookies.

title: sausage-broccoli quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, approximately 1 hour or until middle doesn't wiggle.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until firm.
Roll into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients except for grated Cheddar cheese. Pour into deep, greased baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top of enchilada mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except rolls.
Separate rolls into squares.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture on a square; bring up all 4 corners to center and twist. Dot with butter and dip in crushed cheese croutons.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Toast pecans using margarine.
Break and let cool.
In a boiler, mix sugar, Karo and water.
Boil until syrup forms a ball when dropped in water that feels like chewing gum.
While syrup is boiling, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and pecans. Beat until mixture is stiff enough to hold up when dropped.
Drop on waxed paper.
When hard, store in tin.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat. In a bowl, stir butter and brown sugar until well combined. Stir in the egg. Beat in the flour, 1/4 c. at a time. Stir in the baking powder, salt, vanilla and walnuts, and mix well. Spread batter evenly in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes, or until top is dry and tester comes out clean.

title: hungarian mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion in butter, salt lightly.
Add mushrooms, 1 teaspoon dill weed, 1/2 cup stock, tamari and paprika.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Melt remaining butter in large saucepan, whisk in flour and cook for a few minutes.
Add milk, stir frequently over low heat for 10 minutes or until thick.
Stir in mushroom mixture and remaining stock.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Just before serving, add salt, pepper, lemon juice, sour cream and extra dill (if desired).
Serve garnished with parsley.
